(2053, 340, 'event_content', '<a href=\"https://point.ccbchurch.com/form_response.php?id=63\">REGISTER ONLINE HERE</a>\r\n\r\nParent Training Day is a one-day conference to equip you with the tools you need to build a strong family focused on Christ.¬† The day will include two large group sessions, and three workshop times.¬† You will have the opportunity to choose from ten workshops covering everything from building a faith foundation in little ones, to launching your teen to college.\r\n\r\n<strong>COST:</strong>\r\nIncludes Lunch catered by Noodles &amp; Co., Snacks &amp; Materials\r\n$8 per Kid Point &amp; Student Point\r\n$15 per adult\r\n$50 Family Max\r\n\r\n<strong>CONFERENCE SCHEDULE:</strong>\r\n\r\n8:45 Kid Check In Opens\r\n<span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_314160830\"><span class=\"aQJ\">9:00-9:45</span></span> Large Group Session 1\r\n<span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_314160831\"><span class=\"aQJ\">10:00- 10:45</span></span> Workshop Session 1\r\n<span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_314160832\"><span class=\"aQJ\">11:00- 11:45</span></span> Workshop Session 2\r\n<span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_314160833\"><span class=\"aQJ\">11:45- 12:30</span></span> Lunch\r\n<span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_314160834\"><span class=\"aQJ\">12:30- 1:15</span></span> Workshop Session 3\r\n<span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_314160835\"><span class=\"aQJ\">1:30 - 2:00</span></span> Large Group Session 2\r\n\r\n<strong>WORKSHOP CHOICES INCLUDE:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Family Devotions 101</strong>\r\nHow to lead family devotions with kids 0-18 years of age\r\n\r\n<strong>Peacemaking Skills for Families</strong>\r\nPractical, truth-based skills for handling family conflict\r\n\r\n<strong>Preparing to Launch</strong>\r\nHow to prepare your teen for college and an independent life\r\n\r\n<strong>Faith Foundations</strong>\r\nFaith-training tools for young families\r\n\r\n<strong>Having THE Talk(s)</strong>\r\nHow to talk to your tweens and teens about healthy relationships, biblical purity, and God‚Äôs plan for marriage and sex\r\n\r\n<strong>Drugs, Porn and Technology, oh my!</strong>\r\nThree conversations every parent needs to have with their teens and tweens\r\n\r\n<strong>Training Kids for Worship</strong>\r\nHow to help your kids engage in and love church\r\n\r\n<strong>Child Dedication</strong>\r\nFor parents deciding to have their child dedicated on <span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_314160836\"><span class=\"aQJ\">November 8th</span></span>\r\n\r\n...and more\r\n\r\n<strong>WHAT WILL MY KIDS BE DOING DURING THE CONFERENCE?</strong>\r\nWe have a dynamic day planned for our nursery through elementary aged children.¬† Toddlers will enjoy play time, crafts, and games. Our Preschool and Elementary kids will experience Camp Kid Point, a full day of crafts, activities, worship and teaching time.¬† Children 2 years old and over will have pizza and fruit for lunch, as well as a snack.\r\n(If you have a gluten or dairy allergy please provide a sack lunch)\r\n\r\nSpace is limited\r\n\r\n<strong>WHAT ABOUT MIDDLE &amp; HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS?</strong>\r\nOur Student Point will have a fun day that has been planned just for them.¬† They will SOAP together, serve in the food pantry, Tie Dye shirts and more.\r\n\r\nStudents will have pizza and fruit for lunch.¬† (If you have a gluten or dairy allergy please provide a sack lunch)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
