(2621, 428, 'welcome_text', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Over the past six months, through various circumstances and conversations, God has been increasingly burdening my heart for people on the north side of Raleigh. At our church‚Äôs 5 year anniversary, I clearly sensed God leading me to step forward and put my YES on the table to leave the comfort of the Raleigh campus and be SENT out to help start another campus. I am so excited to see what God is already doing in bringing various pieces together for the launch of this new campus in North Raleigh.</p>\r\n- Bill Finley, <em>Campus Pastor</em>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>The Timeline</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<strong>November 15</strong>¬†- Launch Team Meeting -¬†Trinity Academy Atrium\r\n<strong>December 6</strong> - Give A Church Christmas Party &amp; Silent Auction -¬†Trinity Academy Atrium\r\n<strong>December 23-24</strong> - Christmas Experience - Inwood Baptist Church\r\n<strong>January 10</strong> - Launch Team Meeting (7:00-8:30) - Trinity Academy Atrium\r\n<strong>January 24</strong> - Preview Service\r\n<strong>February 7</strong> - Launch Team Meeting (7:00-8:30)- Trinity Academy Atrium\r\n<strong>February 28</strong> - Preview Service\r\n<strong>March 13</strong> - Practice Service in Final Location\r\n<strong>March 20</strong> - LAUNCH SUNDAY\r\n\r\nIf you want to be a part of pointing people to Jesus in North Raleigh, join us at one of our Launch Team Meetings. We will be sharing the latest news and updates along with what God is doing with this campus. Just email Bill Finley at <a href=\"mailto:billf@pointchurch.com\">billf@pointchurch.com</a> if you\'d like to attend. Childcare is always provided.'),
