(6445, 1012, 'when_do_i_get_there', 'It‚Äôs always a good idea to arrive 15 minutes early to find a parking spot, get some coffee, check your kids into Kid Point, and find a seat.'),
(6446, 1012, '_when_do_i_get_there', 'field_55c395edea775'),
(6447, 1012, 'where_do_i_park', 'The driveway to the church is between McDonald\'s and Valero from Glenwood Ave. As you approach the church, take a left and follow the signs to the New Visitor Parking. Those spots are reserved for you.'),
(6448, 1012, '_where_do_i_park', 'field_55c39618ea776'),
(6449, 1012, 'what_should_i_wear', 'You‚Äôre invited to come as you are, whether it‚Äôs a suit or shorts you feel most comfortable wearing. We tend to dress pretty casual.'),
(6450, 1012, '_what_should_i_wear', 'field_55c39637ea777'),
(6451, 1012, 'what_do_i_do_with_my_kids', 'Kid Point is our children‚Äôs program for birth-5th grade. When you walk through the doors you will see a Kid Point sign ahead and on your right. Just follow the Kid Point Signs to the Check-In Table, and our great Kid Point Volunteers will register your kids so that they can have safe and fun Sunday learning about Jesus.\r\n\r\nStudent Point is our program for Middle School and High School students. Student Point at North Raleigh meets at 9:15am on Sundays during first service. For more information, email <a href=\"mailto:jonb@pointchurch.com\">jonb@pointchurch.com</a>.'),
