(66, 1, '2015-08-10 19:52:29', '2015-08-10 19:52:29', '<h3>Need Food Assistance?</h3>\r\nThe Point¬†Food Pantry serves families in need of food assistance by providing a couple of bags of groceries, a hot meal, and clothing every <strong>Saturday from 11:00 am to 12:00 pm.</strong> Families must live in Wake County and arrive no earlier than 10am on Saturday mornings. Assistance is given on a first come, first served basis.\r\n<h4>The food pantry is located in three locations:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Cary:¬†<strong>1503 Walnut St, Cary NC</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Apex:¬†<strong>1402 E Williams St,¬†Apex NC</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Raleigh:¬†<strong>3700 Lake Wheeler Rd, Raleigh NC</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nContact us at 919-467-9159.\r\n\r\nMembers of The Point Church are welcome to receive assistance on Fridays from 4:00 pm to 5:00 pm. Email Jensen Davis at <a href=\"mailto:jensend@pointchurch.com\">jensend@pointchurch.com</a>¬†to make arrangements.\r\n<a name=\"volunteer\"></a>\r\n<h3>Want to Volunteer?</h3>\r\nThanks for your interest in serving at our Care Center! We have many opportunities available. You will likely be scheduled to serve only once in a month (unless you want to do more!). Please fill out <a href=\"http://localhost:8000/pageredir/785\">this¬†form</a>¬†so we can learn more about your interests and availability. Once you submit the form, someone from our Care Ministry team will follow up to speak with you further. We‚Äôre excited for what God is going to do through you in our Care Ministry!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Weekend Opportunities:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Care Center</strong>- Come serve as a volunteer or leader at one of our three Care Centers (South Raleigh, Apex, Cary). Our Care Centers are open from 11am-noon every Saturday. An array of different opportunities are available to fit your passions and skill set. Volunteers and leaders arrive at 9:30am and are normally done by 12:30pm. </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Data Entry</strong>- There are opportunities available to assist with data entry during the week. Often, this is done on Mondays at our Cary Campus but times can be flexible. </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Food Runners</strong>- These volunteers will use our box truck to transport the bags of food from our Apex storage area to our Cary and South Raleigh campuses on Saturday mornings. This can also be done any time on Fridays, depending on a volunteer team‚Äôs availability. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Weekday Opportunities:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Shoppers</strong>- We need shoppers to visit the Eastern NC Food Bank in Raleigh on Mondays. This role includes gathering needed food items at the Food Bank warehouse and transporting the products to our Apex and Cary locations. We are looking to build volunteer teams of 3-4 people. This is normally done on Mondays from 9am-12pm, however some Tuesdays may be required. Preferably, volunteers will be comfortable lifting up to 25lbs and driving a box truck. </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Grocery Donation Pickup-</strong>¬†We are blessed to receive food donations from several area grocery stores! Pickup times vary but are normally on weekday mornings. </span></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Grocery Baggers</strong>- If you‚Äôve served with us on a Saturday, you‚Äôve seen the paper bags full of groceries we provide to our guests each week. We currently distribute nearly 400 bags each week! These bags are filled with products each Thursday evening from 6:30-8pm at our Apex Campus. We are looking to form teams of 7-8 volunteers. Each team will prepare grocery bags once a month.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nQuestions about The Point Care Pantry? Email Jensen Davis at <a href=\"mailto:jensend@pointchurch.com\">jensend@pointchurch.com</a> for more information.', 'Care Pantry', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'care-pantry', '', '', '2017-03-12 10:44:46', '2017-03-12 15:44:46', '', 60, 'http://localhost:8888/point-church/?page_id=66', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(68, 1, '2015-08-10 19:52:38', '2015-08-10 19:52:38', 'We provide clothing through weekly distribution at the Care Pantry and through a partnership with Thrift 2 Gift at our Apex Location.\r\n\r\nYou can shop at Thrift 2 Gift or make a donation at 1402 E Williams St, Apex, NC 27539. They are open Mon-Sat, 10am-5pm.\r\n\r\nYou can donate to our free clothing distribution on Sunday mornings in the lobby.\r\n\r\nIf you need free clothing, just visit the Care Pantry.', 'Care Closet', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'care-closet', '', '', '2015-08-11 06:51:43', '2015-08-11 06:51:43', '', 60, 'http://localhost:8888/point-church/?page_id=68', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(70, 1, '2015-08-10 19:52:55', '2015-08-10 19:52:55', 'Through the <b>Care Fund</b> we provide <i>financial assistance</i> for those who need it in emergencies. We want to be there for you if you are in a time of need and provide longer term support.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in submitting a request for assistance please download this <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1W4DuXQ866-9uqmefRhvuG5t2Dp5RQA1AyjJfQ1f_czY/edit\" target=\"_blank\">Request For Assistance Form</a>. You can fill it out, scan it, and email it to <a href=\"mailto:hannahl@pointchurch.com\">hannahl@pointchurch.com</a> or bring it by our offices Tuesday-Friday at normal business hours at 1503 Walnut St. Cary, NC 27511. Please allow 10 days for your application to be processed.', 'Care Fund', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'care-fund', '', '', '2017-03-09 16:56:24', '2017-03-09 21:56:24', '', 60, 'http://localhost:8888/point-church/?page_id=70', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(72, 1, '2015-08-10 19:53:05', '2015-08-10 19:53:05', 'We offer a variety of Care Classes that meet throughout the year. The classes deal with subjects like addiction, grief, divorce, finances, and parenting among other subjects.\r\n<h3>Jobs for Life</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n[embed]https://vimeo.com/198352673[/embed]\r\n<h4><b>Who:</b></h4>\r\nVolunteers, we are looking for people to help in many different ways with putting the class on. Students, this class is for anyone who would like to work to establish steady and consistent work in their life\r\n<h4><b>What:¬†</b></h4>\r\nJobs For Life is a national organization that partners with churches to restore people\'s lives through the dignity of work\r\n<div></div>\r\n<h4><b>When:¬†</b></h4>\r\nClasses are <span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_1787450214\"><span class=\"aQJ\">on Tue</span></span> &amp; Thu starting <span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_1787450215\"><span class=\"aQJ\">Feb 28th</span></span> for eight weeks; The Interest Meeting will be <span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_1787450216\"><span class=\"aQJ\">January 22nd at 5:30 pm</span></span>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<h4><b>Where:¬†</b></h4>\r\nBoth the Interest Meeting and the classes will be held at the Cary building at <a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/1503+Walnut+St,+Cary,+NC+27511/@35.7653649,-78.7532953,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x89acf36319c49fbd:0xff34d39d17fadade!8m2!3d35.7653606!4d-78.7511066\">1503 Walnut St. Cary, NC 27511</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in helping or finding out more you can contact Jay Cook at <a href=\"mailto:jay@pointchurch.com\">jay@pointchurch.com</a>.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4>Application</h4>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/ApplicantBackgroundInformationForm-1.docx\">Click here to download and print the Application Form (.docx).</a>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Care Classes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'care-classes', '', '', '2017-01-15 10:06:20', '2017-01-15 15:06:20', '', 60, 'http://localhost:8888/point-church/?page_id=72', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(74, 1, '2015-08-10 19:53:16', '2015-08-10 19:53:16', 'We are all about pointing people to Jesus and seeing them take steps and sometimes one of those steps is to go through the process of restoration. We believe that counseling is a great way to see people experience healing and restoration in a deep and lasting way. Here at The Point we are excited to be able to offer many kinds of counseling.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://point.ccbchurch.com/form_response.php?id=32\">Fill out this form¬†</a>if you would like to request pastoral, professional, or premarital counseling.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Pastoral Counseling</h3>\r\nWe work with the pastors and elders of The Point Church to provide pastoral counseling. They are responsible for shepherding the church. Therefore, if you are going through something and would like to speak to a pastor or an elder from your campus, <a href=\"https://point.ccbchurch.com/form_response.php?id=32\">fill out this¬†form</a> or email Jay Cook, the Care Pastor at <a href=\"mailto:jay@pointchurch.com\">jay@pointchurch.com</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Professional Counseling</h3>\r\nThe Point Care Center is excited to be able to offer first rate professional counseling aimed at pointing people to Jesus and helping them to experience spiritual and emotional healing. If you are interested in meeting with a counselor, <a href=\"https://point.ccbchurch.com/form_response.php?id=32\">fill out this form</a>. We offer reduced rates for Point Church members. If you need financial assistance, please indicate that in the form as well.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Premarital Counseling</h3>\r\nWith <b>Premarital Counseling</b> we want to come along side you as you are getting ready to get married and help prepare you for that step in your life. We believe very strongly that premarital counseling helps build stronger marriages. If you are interested in premarital counseling. Download and fill out the <a href=\"http://www.pointchurch.com/filerequest/2331\"><b>Marriage Request Form</b></a> and email it or drop it off with Jay Cook <b>jay@pointchurch.com</b><b>.</b> You can also call if you have any questions (919) 610-9665.\r\n<h3>Counseling Team</h3>\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-94\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/point-church/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/kelly-harrison-300x250.jpeg\" alt=\"kelly-harrison\" width=\"300\" height=\"250\" />Kelly Harrison -¬†Licensed Professional Counselor (LPC)</h4>\r\nCounseling is a journey that can lead to incredible growth and healing in your interpersonal and interpersonal relationships. I enjoy working with individuals, adolescents, couples, and families addressing a variety of issues, including depression, anxiety, grief and loss, adjustment difficulties, trauma, abuse, communication, stress management, spiritual matters, women\'s issues, relationship distress, and family therapy.\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-96\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/point-church/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/jay-cook-300x250.jpeg\" alt=\"jay-cook\" width=\"300\" height=\"250\" />Jay Cook -¬†Care Pastor &amp; Counselor (MCE)</h4>\r\nJay has a Masters in Arts and Christian Education with a concentration in Counseling and Chaplaincy. He is currently completing his Masters in Professional Counseling from Liberty University to be a LPC and has a huge heart to help people experience healing.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Care Counseling', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'care-counseling', '', '', '2015-08-19 20:45:50', '2015-08-19 20:45:50', '', 60, 'http://localhost:8888/point-church/?page_id=74', 0, 'page', '', 0),
