(106, 1, '2015-08-10 21:08:44', '2015-08-10 21:08:44', '<h3>Kids</h3>\r\nWe believe families are our first mission field and place a high priority on making sure your kids have an awesome experience on Sunday mornings. Not only will they be safe and secure, Kid Point uses age-appropriate teaching styles to point your kids to Jesus. Your kids will be begging to come back.\r\n\r\nWe also believe that Sundays are just one part of your child‚Äôs faith training, so we partner with parents to help you be the primary faith trainer. Our Family Discipleship Plan guides families through this lifelong process. We come alongside you to equip you with tools like take home worksheets that you can use to discuss the Bible with your kids. We have an annual parent training day guide you through the stage your child is going through.\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Contact Info</h3>\r\nTo get more info about our upcoming events or meet with one of our leaders, just contact <a href=\"mailto:info@pointchurch.com\">info@pointchurch.com</a> or call 919-467-9159.', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'kidpoint', '', '', '2016-05-27 08:50:12', '2016-05-27 13:50:12', '', 10, 'http://localhost:8888/point-church/?page_id=106', 1, 'page', '', 0),
(108, 1, '2015-08-10 21:26:40', '2015-08-10 21:26:40', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><em><span style=\"color: #00a0c6;\">\"For the earth will be filled with the knowledge of the glory of the Lord as the waters cover the sea.\"</span></em></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #00a0c6;\">- Habakkuk 2:14</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdzyujNLYgZ8H5_lF_tbjsABJQw82Zotu92XMJrEf6s0oYKvA/viewform\">Apply Here Today!</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>United States</h3>\r\nEvery year we partner the Carolina Movement our church planting coaltion to help plant a new church in the United States, specifically North Carolina. ¬†Each fall we take a weekend mission trip to help the new church get off the ground.\r\n\r\nIn the past, we have worked with many church planting organizations to help churches across the USA. In 2013, we worked with Christ\'s Church Albany in Albany, NY, in 2014, we partnered with Canvas Church in Winchester, VA, and in 2015 we worked with Good News Church in Columbus, Ohio. In 2016, we went to Augusta, GA to help Venture Church get up and running. We took trips to these cities to do outreaches and provide volunteers for their weekend services.\r\n\r\nThis year,¬†we have partnered with several churches already, including Journey Church in Havelock, NC and NewCity Church in Raleigh. We look forward to working with more!\r\n\r\nGo to <a href=\"http://localhost:8000/usa\">pointchurch.com/usa</a> for more information, and to sign up for upcoming opportunities.\r\n<h3>Dominican Republic</h3>\r\nWe partner with Rueben and Vicky Dominguez who started H.O.P.E. Dominican Republic. They are committed to bring Christ centered transformation to the Dominican Republic through church planting and meeting the needs of needy children. They have planted two churches and have opened a feeding and education center for 100 children. <a href=\"http://hope4drnow.org/\">Get more information here.</a>\r\n\r\nWe are now working with them to plant a church in Puerto Plata. We look forward to visiting this community on our next trip. Contact Elise at elise@pointchurch.com for more info!\r\n<h3>India</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Central India Christian Mission </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">is our partner in India. They respond to the needs of the people in central and northern India through church planting, medical care, disaster relief, and discipleship. They have planted more than 1400 churches and baptized more than 400,000 people. With CICM we are working in Northern India¬†to plant churches and sponsor children in poverty.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://indiamission.org/\">indiamission.org/</a>\r\n<h3>Middle East</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Canaan Project is located in a primarily Muslim Country in the Middle East and is focused on community development. It provides clean drinking water, technology centers, and schools for girls. The work is supported through a recognized NGO. One family from the church currently lives and works with this unreached people group. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Through CICM we are able to sponsor refugee children from this unreached people group. </span>\r\n\r\nTo get more involved with the Canaan Project email Chris Gregory at<b> <a href=\"mailto:drcg35@nc.rr.com\">drcg35@nc.rr.com</a>.</b>', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'globalmissions', '', '', '2017-03-09 09:50:01', '2017-03-09 14:50:01', '', 10, 'http://localhost:8888/point-church/?page_id=108', 6, 'page', '', 0),
