(113, 1, '2015-08-10 21:57:06', '2015-08-10 21:57:06', 'The goal of our worship services is simple; to worship God. ¬†Our goal is that you can leave honestly saying that I heard from God today and I worshiped him. ¬†We also want every person to have opportunities to participate in worship and not just be a spectator. ¬†Every week you will have the opportunity to sing, take communion, pray, give, and be challenged to take a step in your walk with God.\r\n\r\nBecause we are always preparing for our next campus we need musicians and technicians in every area. ¬†If you can click a mouse, ¬†play the bass, or sing a song, ¬†we would love to hear from you.\r\n\r\nFor more information please contact us - <a href=\"mailto:info@pointchurch.com\">info@pointchurch.com</a>.', 'Experience - Worship', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'experience', '', '', '2015-08-13 00:31:13', '2015-08-13 00:31:13', '', 8, 'http://localhost:8888/point-church/?page_id=113', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(115, 1, '2015-08-10 21:57:47', '2015-08-10 21:57:47', 'There is a reason we call these groups Life Groups instead of small groups. An average small group might get together and talk about the Bible in a comfortable setting, but not take their relationships any further. The goal of a Life Group is to literally <b>DO LIFE TOGETHER</b>! Below is a list of things you will see in every Life Group.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>Eat Together</b> - There\'s something special about sharing a meal together</li>\r\n	<li><b>Study Together</b> - Engaging in discussions of scripture and its application</li>\r\n	<li><b>Share Together</b> - Building friendships and sharing in one another\'s lives</li>\r\n	<li><b>Pray Together</b> - Talking to God on behalf of those in and outside the group</li>\r\n	<li><b>Serve Together</b> - Contributing our part to those in and outside the group</li>\r\n	<li><b>Play Together </b>- Group should be getting together frequently for social events</li>\r\n	<li><b>Multiply Together</b> - Adding people and developing new leaders to start new groups</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"https://point.ccbchurch.com/w_group_list.php\">Click here to find a life group!</a>', 'Connect - Life Groups', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'connect', '', '', '2015-09-11 19:02:19', '2015-09-11 19:02:19', '', 8, 'http://localhost:8888/point-church/?page_id=115', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(117, 1, '2015-08-10 21:58:25', '2015-08-10 21:58:25', 'Service is a big deal in the growth of a Christ Follower. The Bible says that the church is like a body and the individual people are like parts of that body. Unless all of the people are doing their part, our body cannot function properly and be effective. Besides, serving with people we love and love us is one of the most fulfilling things we could possibly do with our time!\r\n\r\nServe Groups function in these areas:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Frontline</strong> - greeting, cafe, ushers, set-up, and tear-down</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Kid Point</strong> - nursery, toddlers, preschool, elementary, security, and check-in</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Student Ministry</strong> - middle school and high school</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Worship</strong> - musicians, vocalists, tech team</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Serve - Service Groups', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'serve', '', '', '2015-08-13 00:31:52', '2015-08-13 00:31:52', '', 8, 'http://localhost:8888/point-church/?page_id=117', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(119, 1, '2015-08-10 22:00:36', '2015-08-10 22:00:36', 'In our experience Core Groups are very similar to a rocket ship. ¬†It is usually when people join one of our Core Groups that their faith explodes and goes to a whole new level.\r\n\r\nCore Groups are meant to be simple yet powerful.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Core Groups are made up of between 2-4 people.</li>\r\n	<li>They are same gender, not co-ed.</li>\r\n	<li>There is no curriculum or workbook.</li>\r\n	<li>Three things are done during the group time:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Accountability questions discussed</li>\r\n	<li>Sharing from weekly Bible reading</li>\r\n	<li>Prayer for those far from God</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nRead below for a more detailed explanation of the three elements of Core Groups and testimonials from people who have been in groups themselves!\r\n<h4>Accountability</h4>\r\nFew things ever get done in life without some degree of accountability. ¬†In pursuit of godliness we need accountability to one another... ¬†The first thing the group does is taking turns answering each of the accountability questions. ¬†The questions are designed to get to the core of each person\'s walk with God. ¬†They are designed to give you a place to discuss what is really going on in a safe and caring environment. ¬†The questions will be a Core Group card that you can keep in your Bible.\r\n<h4>Scripture Reading</h4>\r\nEach group member commits to reading through the books of the Bible. ¬†The goal is to get an appetite for God\'s word. ¬†God\'s word like coffee is an acquired taste, the more you get, the more you enjoy it. ¬†Before long you can\'t get enough! ¬†The reading needs to be enough that it gives God time to speak. ¬†A daily devotional of a few verses for the day is not enough time for the Spirit to really work on your heart.\r\n\r\nWhen the group comes together the next week, they ask each other if they have completed the reading. ¬†If any group member has not finished, then the whole group reads the same scripture again the next week. ¬†This is not a bad thing; believe that God still has something he wants to show you in that section of the Word.\r\n<h4>Praying for those far from God</h4>\r\nIf we really believe that the eternal destiny of the people we love depends of their knowing Jesus Christ, their salvation should be continually at the top of the things we pray for. Each person in the core group should identify several people far from God and pray for them by name to meet Christ. List each person\'s\r\n\r\nname, the group member who knows them, and something about the person to help you to pray on the provided card. ¬†Pray for them by name at the end of the Core Group time. Also, you can pick a person to pray for each day during your time with God.', 'Grow - Core Groups', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'grow', '', '', '2015-08-13 00:30:39', '2015-08-13 00:30:39', '', 8, 'http://localhost:8888/point-church/?page_id=119', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(121, 1, '2015-08-10 22:01:16', '2015-08-10 22:01:16', 'Jesus came to lead people to God. If we are called to become more like Him, we must also lead others to follow Him. ¬†The last step in the Path is to use the influence God has given you to invest in the lives of others and invite them to take their next step with Christ. A great way to lead is to become a leader at our church.\r\n\r\nSome position of leadership at our church include: Life Group Leader, Serve Group Leader, Worship Leader, or Mission Leader. You can also lead by going through the Bible using the S.O.A.P method.\r\n\r\nWe invest in leaders and potential leaders through our regular Leadership Community. Don\'t miss these!', 'Lead - Leadership', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lead', '', '', '2015-08-13 00:31:33', '2015-08-13 00:31:33', '', 8, 'http://localhost:8888/point-church/?page_id=121', 0, 'page', '', 0),
