(884, 4, '2017-01-05 08:17:31', '2017-01-05 13:17:31', '<strong>S for Scripture: Mark 4:20</strong>\r\n\r\n‚ÄúBut those (the seeds) that were sown on the good soil are the ones who hear the\r\nword and accept it and bear fruit, thirtyfold and sixtyfold and a hundredfold.‚Äù\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>O for Observation:</strong>\r\n\r\nSatan, persecution, affliction, the cares of this world and more will render me\r\nunfruitful. The ‚ÄúBut‚Äù in verse 20 shows a contrast between the first three soils and this fourth ‚Äì the ‚Äúgood soil.‚Äù This verse draws me to John 15:1-8 where Jesus speaks about abiding in Him, bearing much fruit, glorifying the Father and proving ‚Äúto be my disciples.‚Äù\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>A for Application:</strong>\r\n\r\nIf I don‚Äôt connect with Jesus early each morning and abide with Him throughout the day - the cares, troubles, busyness, deceitfulness and distractions of this world will choke out my fruitfulness. I must keep my heart pure (Proverbs 4:23) and allow God‚Äôs word to transform my mind (Romans 12:2) so that I can stay focused on my mission. I must abide in Jesus (John 15:4) to bear fruit. I must take the initiative to B.L.E.S.S. people and make the most of every opportunity. I cannot accomplish the work of the Spirit in the power of the flesh, so I must be continuously filled with the Holy Spirit (Ephesians 5:18).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>P for Prayer:</strong>\r\n\r\nForgive me Lord for not bearing all of the fruit that you created me to bear. I confess that I am often far too occupied by the good things that keep me away from your ultimate tasks and mission. Forgive me for my timidity, my lack of discipline, my out of balanced priorities and my concern of what others may think.\r\n\r\nLord, You have sown good seed into me, and I want my life to be good soil - bearing fruit a hundredfold! Keep ‚Äúthe cares of the world and the deceitfulness of riches and the desires for other things‚Äù from entering in, choking the word, and making me unfruitful. (Mark 4:19)\r\n\r\nI have an enemy who is working in a myriad of ways to steal, kill, and destroy my fruitfulness. Thank you Lord that your word says, ‚ÄúGreater is He that is in you than he that is in this world.‚Äù (I John 4:4). Lord Jesus you are in me. Holy Spirit, You are in me. Jesus, you said ‚ÄúHow much more will the Father give the Spirit to those who ask.‚Äù (Luke 11:13). So Father, I‚Äôm asking you to give me, and fill me again today with your Spirit ‚Äì Your love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, gentleness, and self-control. Give me your your wisdom, courage, grace, discernment, truth and power so when the devil and his agents try to squeeze me like an orange ‚Äì I will drip Jesus!\r\n\r\nJesus, empower me today to represent you well and to re-present you correctly to those I encounter who have swallowed the enemy‚Äôs lies about you. You call me the\r\n‚Äúsalt of the earth‚Äù and the ‚Äúlight of this world‚Äù ‚Äì let me season the environment and shine your light of truth with those I engage today.', 'S.O.A.P. | Mark 4', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 's-o-a-p-mark-4', '', '', '2017-01-05 08:24:37', '2017-01-05 13:24:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=884', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(886, 4, '2017-01-06 08:09:56', '2017-01-06 13:09:56', '<strong>S for Scripture: Mark 5:6-7, 22-23, 25, 27-28</strong>\r\n\r\n6 ‚ÄúWhen he [the demon-possessed man] saw Jesus from a distance, he ran and fell on his knees in front of him. 7 He shouted at the top of his voice, ‚ÄòWhat do you want with me, Jesus, Son of the Most High God? In God‚Äôs name don‚Äôt torture me!‚Äô‚Äù\r\n\r\n22 ‚ÄúThen one of the synagogue leaders, named Jairus, came, and when he saw Jesus, he fell at his feet. 23 He pleaded earnestly with him, ‚ÄòMy little daughter is dying. Please come and put your hands on her so that she will be healed and live.‚Äô‚Äù\r\n\r\n25 ‚ÄúAnd a woman was there who had been subject to bleeding for twelve years. 27 When she heard about Jesus, she came up behind him in the crowd and touched his cloak, 28 because she thought, ‚ÄòIf I just touch his clothes, I will be healed.‚Äô‚Äù\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>O for Observation:</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Gospel of Mark is full of great stories of healing like these. Three amazing miracles occur in Mark 5: demons are cast out; 12 years of bleeding is stopped; and a young girl is raised to life. Much could be said about these. What jumps out to me is how these people come to Jesus. The demoniac sees Jesus from afar, runs to him, falls to his knees, and cries out in a loud voice for mercy. The religious leader humbled himself and came to Jesus. Falling on his knees, he too begs Jesus for help. The woman, fearful of being humiliated and rejected by the crowd, also came up to Jesus. In fact, she sneaks up on him and in faith touches him. In each case miraculous healing occurs through their faith. Yet, in each case, they must also humbly come to Jesus.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>A for Application:</strong>\r\n\r\nNo problem I carry, or anyone else carries, is too big for Jesus. I must humble myself and go to Jesus for His help. I must point others to Jesus, and help them take a step of faith to ask for His help.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>P for Prayer:</strong>\r\n\r\nLord Jesus, humbly I come to You. I need You each day to live as I should, to walk in health and wholeness ‚Äì physically and spiritually. I come to You as we plant the new Point Church in Fuquay-Varina. Help me/us point people to You, so that they may also come humbly and in faith and find wholeness in You!', 'S.O.A.P. | Mark 5', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 's-o-a-p-mark-5', '', '', '2017-01-06 08:15:08', '2017-01-06 13:15:08', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=886', 0, 'post', '', 0),
