(904, 4, '2017-01-10 08:15:00', '2017-01-10 13:15:00', '<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>S for Scripture: Mark 7:6-7</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<sup>6</sup> He replied, ‚ÄúIsaiah was right when he prophesied about you hypocrites; as it is written: ‚Äú‚ÄòThese people honor me with their lips but their hearts are far from me. <sup>7</sup> They worship me in vain; their teachings are merely human rules.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>O for Observation:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nThe Pharisees and Scribes were concerned with the fact that the disciples did not wash before meals. Jesus points out that what you do (your physical actions) should never become more important than the heart behind the actions. Jesus makes clear that your actions can look like you are close to God but in reality your heart can be miles from him.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>A for Application:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nEverything I do, even if it is outwardly religious and ‚Äúgood,\" can be done without a hint of love and adoration for God. I can look holy, even though my heart is far from God. The world might not notice, but to God the heart is the most important (1 Samuel 16:1-13). Today, assess why you are doing the \"good\" that you are doing. If it is for selfish ambition and vain conceit, remember the cross (the love of Jesus that resulted in action for you) and recenter yourself.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>P for Prayer:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nFather, help me do good today but, more than anything, help my actions today be in response to the good you have done for me. Make me mindful of why I do what I do and allow me to surrender all of my gross, selfish intentions to you. Remind me constantly of your cross and fill my heart with gratitude. Help me make today count for eternity. Amen.', 'S.O.A.P. | Mark 7', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 's-o-a-p-mark-7', '', '', '2017-01-10 08:15:00', '2017-01-10 13:15:00', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=904', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(906, 4, '2017-01-11 07:01:59', '2017-01-11 12:01:59', '<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>S for Scripture: Mark 8:17-18</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<sup>17</sup> And Jesus, aware of this, said to them, ‚ÄúWhy are you discussing the fact that you have no bread? Do you not yet perceive or understand? Are your hearts hardened? <sup>18</sup> Having eyes do you not see, and having ears do you not hear? And do you not remember?‚Äù\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>O for Observation:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nAt this point, this is the THIRD time that the disciples have been in a situation where they are questioning whether they will have enough food. Twice before Jesus had taken small amounts of bread and fish and multiplied them into more than enough for large groups of people. Despite having personally seen these miracles, the disciples still questioned what would happen and if it could be done. After the first miracle, they assumed it was a one-time thing. And now, the third time this situation has come up, they still don‚Äôt seem to be catching on. Jesus‚Äô act of reproducing a similar miracle at different times speaks to God‚Äôs character and faithfulness. Miracles are not the exception; they are the rule. The disciples had recently seen Jesus do this, twice. Instead of doubting, they should have expected Jesus to do something great.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>A for Application:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nHow many times have I seen God pull through in tough, seemingly impossible situations? It‚Äôs happened multiple times in my life and in the lives of my friends and family. I‚Äôve seen Him provide when resources were depleted. I‚Äôve seen Him heal when doctors can‚Äôt explain it. I‚Äôve seen broken marriages restored, long awaited babies arrive in perfect timing, and prayers for family members who are far from God be answered in miraculous ways. Yet somehow, each time a new trial arrives, I‚Äôm quick to lose my memory. I‚Äôm like the disciples. I forget how God worked, the miracles I‚Äôve seen, and I start to worry. I start to question if God will pull through THIS time.\r\n\r\nI need to spend more time in the Word, getting to know God‚Äôs character, more time listening to other people‚Äôs stories, and more time sharing my own. This will help me keep what God is doing in the forefront of my mind.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>P for Prayer:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nFather, thank you for being steady, true, and unchanging even when I forget what you‚Äôve done. Thank you for providing faithfully and working EVERY time. Forgive me for my lack of confidence in you and my short-term memory of your work in my life. Please give me opportunities to share stories of your faithfulness and listen to how you‚Äôre working in other people‚Äôs lives. Give me a deeper capacity to remember and rely on knowledge of your past faithfulness. Help me to use that as a catalyst for confidence in your faithfulness now and in the future. In Jesus‚Äô name, Amen.', 'S.O.A.P. | Mark 8', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 's-o-a-p-mark-8', '', '', '2017-01-11 07:01:59', '2017-01-11 12:01:59', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=906', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(907, 4, '2017-01-12 07:55:21', '2017-01-12 12:55:21', '<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>S for Scripture: Mark 9:28-29</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<sup>28</sup> After Jesus had gone indoors, his disciples asked him privately, ‚ÄúWhy couldn‚Äôt we drive it out?‚Äù¬†<sup>29</sup>¬†He replied, ‚ÄúThis kind can come out only by prayer.‚Äù\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>O for Observation:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nEarlier in Mark 9, Jesus pulls away with three of his disciples to a secluded mountain where he reveals himself to them in more personal and powerful ways than ever before. Jesus returns with these three back down the mountain and is greeted by the chaos of everyday life: he encounters the other nine disciples surrounded by a large crowd, including some of his most intense opponents (‚Äúscribes‚Äù). They are arguing with one another over a demon-possessed boy who cannot speak. They had brought the boy to the nine disciples, but they could not heal him. Jesus heals the boy and rebukes the crowd (including the nine disciples) for their lack of faith. Afterwards, in a private moment with his disciples, Jesus explains why they could not cast out the demon and heal the boy: a lack of¬†‚Äúprayer.‚Äù There failure lay in their reliance upon their own strength rather than the power of God. When overwhelmed by the powers and difficulties of this world, true FAITH directs our attention away from ourselves to God. Faith joined with PRAYER connects us more intimately with the ONE who has the power to defeat demons and heal the brokenness of this fallen world.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>A for Application:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nThis story exposes my true priorities: there are times when spending time alone WITH God is LESS important doing things FOR God? And it challenges me to examine how I¬†prioritize¬†my time in a way that places God as my HIGHEST priority. If Jesus is my great REWARD, I will trust him and turn to him in situations that threaten to defeat and overwhelm me. I am challenged to develop better ROUTINES of prayer and communion with God throughout my days and weeks . . . as Jesus modeled in his personal walk with God (Mark 1:35-37) and in his public walk with his¬†disciples (Mark 9:2-13).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>P for Prayer:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nJesus, you are my great treasure and reward. I will seek you with all of my heart by developing a consistent routine of prayer . . . seeking your face consistently in the early morning and throughout the day. I am so thankful that I am not alone to face the challenges and pressures of this world and life alone. Thank your for being my Emmanuel . . . a very present help in trouble . . . my great reward.', 'S.O.A.P. | Mark 9', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 's-o-a-p-mark-9', '', '', '2017-01-12 07:55:21', '2017-01-12 12:55:21', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=907', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(908, 4, '2017-01-13 07:55:46', '2017-01-13 12:55:46', '<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>S for Scripture: Mark 10:14-15</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<sup>14</sup> When Jesus saw this, he was indignant. He said to them,¬†‚ÄúLet the little children come to me, and do not hinder them, for the kingdom of God belongs to such as these. <sup>15</sup> Truly I tell you, anyone who will not receive the kingdom of God like a little child will never enter it.‚Äù\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>O for Observation:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nJesus always acts in a timely manner. Every detail of my life is under his scrutiny. This passage is a typical scenario where the parents identify that Jesus has something special to give to their children. That special something is His blessing. Probably a prayer. The disciples react, because they are aware of the Master¬¥s itinerary and want to protect his busy schedule. Children don¬¥t bother Him at all, though. Quite the contrary, He seizes the moment, to leave a fundamental principle for eternity. It is: whoever wants to enter to the Kingdom of God and does not do it as a child, will never enter in it.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>A for Application:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nLet‚Äôs meditate seriously on how a child is. A child is sincere, transparent, innocent and expressive in the moment. Their antics make us‚Äìparents, lose our patience many times. What they are doing is just showing their own reality, obviously immature. That behavior does not mean they should be despised or made less. It is urgent that every adult learns from our children that spontaneity to be surprised with those little things in life and cultivate their sweetness. There are so many miracles happening around us, that we have stopped appreciating, for not having the eyes of innocence of that restless child -yes, but simple in its expression. Here is our call: No longer to be calculating or prejudiced.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>P for Prayer:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nBlessed God, I thank you infinitely for making me know this essential principle to enter into your holy and blessed Kingdom. I must be like a child, not just because of his innocence or naivete. Beyond that, what I should long to have is a heart of love, forgiveness, tenderness, sweetness and sincerity that I have lost through the years of life. Help me to place myself in the dimension of a child, and thus, not lose the blessing of being by your side for all eternity. In the name of Christ I have prayed. Amen.', 'S.O.A.P. | Mark 10', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 's-o-a-p-mark-10', '', '', '2017-01-13 07:58:19', '2017-01-13 12:58:19', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=908', 0, 'post', '', 0),
