(918, 3, '2017-01-15 22:45:45', '2017-01-16 03:45:45', '<b>S for¬†Scripture: Mark 11:25</b>\r\n\r\n25 And when you stand praying, if you hold anything against anyone, forgive them, so that your Father in heaven may forgive you your sins\r\n\r\n<b>O for Observation:</b>\r\n\r\nIn one sense, forgiveness from God is conditional on that we forgive others. I haven‚Äôt heard people talk about this much but Jesus is pretty clear. It‚Äôs not an option.\r\n\r\n<b>A for Application:</b>\r\n\r\nI need to make sure I‚Äôve forgiven anyone that I‚Äôm harboring bitterness, anger, frustration, or unforgiveness towards. I must do this each day. I should reflect on this regularly so that I don‚Äôt let unforgiveness build up towards anyone.\r\n\r\n<b>P for Prayer:</b>\r\n\r\nLord, you‚Äôve forgiven me for so much. Out of this love I ought to love much and forgive much. I am not entitled to anger, get bitter, or hold grudges. Spirit, speak to me, show me if I‚Äôm holding on and need to forgive someone. In Jesus‚Äô name, amen.', 'S.O.A.P. | Mark 11', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 's-o-a-p-mark-11', '', '', '2017-01-15 22:49:25', '2017-01-16 03:49:25', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=918', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(921, 4, '2017-01-18 07:57:02', '2017-01-18 12:57:02', '<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>S for Scripture: Mark 13:10</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<sup>10</sup> \"And the gospel must first be preached to all the nations.‚Äù\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>O for Observation:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nIn this passage, Jesus has returned to Jerusalem one last time. He has been busy teaching his disciples and being tested by the religious leaders. He has just told his disciples the temple would be destroyed, and, when they were alone, they asked him when and how it would happen. In Mark‚Äôs gospel, he doesn‚Äôt actually answer them, but rather talks about the time leading up to when he will return as the Lion, saving his allies, and destroying his enemies. In the middle of this teaching, he gives a preliminary condition for any of this happening--the gospel must first be preached to all nations. The word ‚Äúnation\" doesn‚Äôt mean countries as I one typically understands it, rather it means \"people groups.\" A people group has their own unique language and culture. He sent them to the WHOLE world, and it took them until after he was gone . . . and then some . . . to understand it.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>A for Application:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nI am also sent to participate in the events leading to Jesus‚Äô return. There are more than 1,700 unreached people groups in the countries of South Asia alone. That means more than one billion people have never even had a chance to hear about Jesus. If I want Christ to return, I must go. There are many reasons to go to India for the cause of Christ, but to aid in his return is a powerful one. Jesus has given me, . . . . give all of us . . . a job to do. How dare we disobey.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>P for Prayer:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nJesus, come quickly. Thank you for your patience with me as I regularly fail to participate in your plan for the nations. Forgive me for fearing to go to the unreached peoples of the world. Give me the courage to participate in your return by going to India and sharing you with others in that nation. You are worth ALL the risk. I love you Jesus. Amen.', 'S.O.A.P. | Mark 13', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 's-o-a-p-mark-13', '', '', '2017-01-18 07:57:02', '2017-01-18 12:57:02', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=921', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(922, 4, '2017-01-17 07:50:43', '2017-01-17 12:50:43', '<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>S for Scripture: Mark 12:42-44</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<sup>42</sup> And a poor widow came and put in two small copper coins, which make a penny. <sup>43</sup> And he called his disciples to him and said to them, ‚ÄúTruly, I say to you, this poor widow has put in more than all those who are contributing to the offering box. <sup>44</sup> For they all contributed out of their abundance, but she out of her poverty has put in everything she had, all she had to live on.‚Äù\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>O for Observation:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nThis woman was not a beneficial member of society, most likely overlooked and disregarded, caught the Master\'s eye and warmed his heart. She could have been timid and inconspicuous, yet Jesus uses her as an example for His kingdom standards. It was not the amount that she gave, yet the condition of her heart that becomes evident. She gave up all of her monetary possession to gain favor in the sight of God.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/image.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-923\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-923 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/image.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" /></a>\r\nIt reminds me of the women in Uganda whom have little, and when the offering time comes at Kisoro Hill Baptist Church, some would bring their shillings and drop them in the baskets and some would bring beautiful, flower covered baskets full of beans. There were even some who could not give beans or potatoes, so they would bring rocks out of their garden. The church had a pile of rocks next to the church, and when asked about it, Pastor Mbonye told us that these were the offerings of the people who could not give anything else, so they brought rocks. And, those rocks will be the foundation of the next church that is built. They had so little money, yet they still gave to the ministry of God.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>A for Application:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nI must set my heart on the words and works of God rather than my monetary accumulations. The blessing of time, talents and treasures that he has given to me must be presented back to Him. They are better off in His hands than mine.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>P for Prayer:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nHoly Father, thank you for taking such good care of your children! You are the giver of life. You are patient and kind with us when we are blind. We humbly ask that Your Spirit continue to work in our lives to live life with open hands rather than closed fists. Everything in our possession is yours to do with as your will sees fit. Open our yes to see the needs around us; open our hands to do your work, and open our hearts to be more like you. In Jesus\' name, Amen', 'S.O.A.P. | Mark 12', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 's-o-a-p-mark-12', '', '', '2017-01-17 07:53:37', '2017-01-17 12:53:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=922', 0, 'post', '', 0),
