(925, 4, '2017-01-19 07:55:54', '2017-01-19 12:55:54', '<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>S for Scripture: Mark 14:37-38</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<sup>37</sup> \"Then he returned to his disciples and found them sleeping. ‚ÄúSimon,‚Äù he said to Peter, ‚Äúare you asleep? Couldn‚Äôt you keep watch for one hour? <sup>37</sup> Watch and pray so that you will not fall into temptation. The spirit is willing, but the flesh is weak.‚Äù\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>O for Observation:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nOn the night he¬†is to be betrayed, Jesus invites Peter along with James and John, his closest friends, to pray for what lies ahead - his crucifixion and suffering for¬†the sins of the world. And when he needs them the most, Jesus returns to find them sleeping, not once, but three times! And here Jesus addresses Peter directly, but not by the new name Jesus gave him, but by his old name, Simon. It wouldn\'t be till after his resurrection, that Jesus reinstates Peter when he asks him three times if he loves him (John 21).\r\n\r\nI also think it is significant that this event takes place right after Jesus tells Peter that he will deny him 3 times (vs. 30) and right before he actually does it (vs.68-71). It makes me wonder if Peter had kept watch and prayed as his Lord requested those 3 times, that he would have had the faith and strength to stand by Jesus and not deny him?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>A for Application:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nIn order to walk with Jesus I must watch and pray. I must continually be looking out for Satan\'s traps, schemes, and any foot holds he might have on my life because I know he prowls about like a roaring lion (1 Peter 5:8). And secondly, I need to continually be in prayer for God\'s will to be done in my life and not my own. My flesh always wants to pursue my selfish dreams and desires, so I must walk by the Spirit (Galatians 5:16). And the key to this is by consistently talking with God through prayer as Jesus did.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>P for Prayer:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nFather, thank you for the gift of your Holy Spirit and for freeing me from the bondages of sin and death! Thank you for choosing me even though I was an enemy of the cross and giving me a new identity as a son in your¬†Kingdom! Forgive me Lord for the times I have fallen asleep and lived as my old self. But please help me to walk in the strength of your Spirit to accomplish your will for my life and not in the weakness of my¬†flesh that wants to fall into sinful slumber. Thank you Lord for your grace, patience, and continual call to live out my identity as a son of God! Amen.', 'S.O.A.P. | Mark 14', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 's-o-a-p-mark-14', '', '', '2017-01-19 07:59:46', '2017-01-19 12:59:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=925', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(931, 4, '2017-01-20 08:06:32', '2017-01-20 13:06:32', '<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>S for Scripture: Mark 15:1</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<sup>1</sup> \"At dawn‚Äôs first light, the high priests, with the religious leaders and scholars, arranged a conference with the entire Jewish Council. After tying Jesus securely, they took him out and presented him to Pilate.‚Äù\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>O for Observation:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nThe thing that sticks out the most to me is the evil and sadness of this chapter. What meant the most to me in this reading of Mark were the moments when Jesus rose early to spend time with his father . . . contrasted with the men in this chapter who rose early to plot against the very God they proclaimed they worshipped. I keep thinking about all the people in Mark who didn‚Äôt recognize the living God right next to them even as he performed miracles. I also can‚Äôt help but wonder if I were there that day, would I be among the scoffers as Jesus was led to his death? I certainly see that in myself sometimes. \r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>A for Application:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nI need to draw closer to Jesus so that I might recognize his voice when he speaks. He has to be the most important voice. And, when he speaks I need to respond in faith that he is in control. I need to make sure that I develop routines of setting aside to be with Jesus in the morning, making space for listening to his leading and waiting to hear his voice. \r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>P for Prayer:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nFather, please convict me of the parts of my life that I think I‚Äôve given to you but are actually hollow vessels for my pride. Teach me to recognize your voice in all the parts of my life. I repent of the sin of believing in anything else for my happiness other than you. Thank you for your son.', 'S.O.A.P. | Mark 15', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 's-o-a-p-mark-15', '', '', '2017-01-20 08:06:32', '2017-01-20 13:06:32', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=931', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(933, 4, '2017-01-21 00:35:06', '2017-01-21 05:35:06', '<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>S for Scripture: Mark 16:8</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<sup>8</sup> \"Trembling and bewildered, the women went out and fled from the tomb. They said nothing to anyone, because they were afraid.‚Äù\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>O for Observation:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nThe resurrection has happened and no one expected it. No one knew it happened. The women went to the tomb to anoint the body of Jesus only to find out there was no body. There was an angel who told them to tell the disciples Jesus was going to meet them in Galilee. Rather than recording their excitement, Mark records their initial shock. They never experienced this and they didn\'t know what to do... or how to explain it. So they did nothing.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>A for Application:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nI have been told, read and experience a story that doesn\'t always make sense. After 20 plus years of following Jesus I still have questions. There are still things I can\'t explain. At times, it would be easy to keep my mouth shut while I process. But that\'s not what I was told to do. Also, when I stop focusing on what I don\'t know, I\'m reminded of what I do know. And that excites me. Then I can\'t stop talking.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #604678;\"><strong>P for Prayer:</strong></span>\r\n\r\nFather, I\'m thankful the ladies didn\'t stay quiet. We know from the other accounts that eventually they did share the good news. But it\'s easy to see why they didn\'t say anything at first. How do you explain something that doesn\'t make sense to you? I pray that I won\'t get bogged down with what I don\'t know but that you would continue to remind me of all you\'ve done and give me boldness and wisdom to share the amazing story with anyone who will listen.', 'S.O.A.P. | Mark 16', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 's-o-a-p-mark-16', '', '', '2017-01-21 00:36:48', '2017-01-21 05:36:48', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=933', 0, 'post', '', 0),
