(984, 4, '2017-02-20 17:29:09', '2017-02-20 22:29:09', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúLet us hold unswervingly to the hope we profess, for he who promises is faithful.‚Äù ‚Äì Hebrews 10:23\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nWe serve a faithful God who has given us his great and precious promises!¬† Therefore, it only makes sense to hold unswervingly to those promises when the circumstances of life storm and rage!\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nIt is easy for me to hold onto the promises of God when everything is sunshine and rainbows.¬† It is when the circumstances of life are overwhelming and threaten to crush me; that is when it is the most difficult for me to stay the course of faith.¬† However, it is also when holding onto faith in God‚Äôs promises that it is the most necessary. I must saturate myself with the promises of God to the point where my first response is not one of <em>fear</em> but <em>faith</em>!\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather God, help me to hide your promises in my heart and to hold unswervingly to my faith in you, because you are faithful!¬† You are a good, good father and you will be with me in every trial and trouble.¬† In the name of Jesus I pray.¬† Amen.', 'Promise #1 ‚Äì Faithfulness', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-1', '', '', '2017-02-22 14:50:03', '2017-02-22 19:50:03', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=984', 0, 'post', '', 0),
