(988, 4, '2017-02-21 09:13:22', '2017-02-21 14:13:22', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúJesus said to her, \'I am the resurrection and the life. The one who believes in me will live, even though they die;and whoever lives by believing in me will never die. Do you believe this?\'‚Äù ‚Äî John 11:25-26\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nMartha had done what was right in her moment of crisis . . . in her moment of deep need: she cried out to Jesus for help! However, he delayed; he put other things before her sick brother Lazarus. Surely this raised doubts in the heart of Mary . . . ‚ÄúDoesn‚Äôt the Lord love her brother Lazarus? Doesn‚Äôt he care for Martha?‚Äù So, when Jesus‚Äô delay resulted in the death of her brother Lazarus, she was confused . . . her faith was faltering and her hope was withering. Jesus revives her faltering faith with a promise of hope: ‚ÄúI am the resurrection and the life. The one who believes in me will live, even though they die.‚Äù\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nI have experienced such times when I needed God and cried out to him in faith . . . and heard nothing but the rapid beating of my heart . . . I felt alone. Yet, I have learned that it takes mature faith to hope in God even when He seems to be neglecting my cries for help . . . when the voice on the other side of the conversation is completely silent. At times like these, I have come to wait and look for Jesus to come to me personally. He does this through a promise . . . like he did for Martha. Again and again I have seen my hope remain strong as faith was nursed through a promise. Like an anchor in a storm and like a life vest for one on the raging seas, God‚Äôs promises keep me rooted in faith and afloat when life‚Äôs crises threaten to pull me under. God‚Äôs promises keeps me hopeful in the storms of life so that I am able to not only survive, but grow into new life through them.\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, faith is simply trusting in your promises. May I be characterized by such faith. Thank you for the hope your promises give to my life. Thank you that You have given me a hope and a future (Jer. 29:11). May this hope free me to more radically love those around me . . . particularly those far from you. Amen.', 'Promise #2 ‚Äì Hope', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-2-hope', '', '', '2017-02-22 14:49:48', '2017-02-22 19:49:48', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=988', 0, 'post', '', 0),
