(991, 4, '2017-02-22 10:31:46', '2017-02-22 15:31:46', '<h3>Blog</h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8000/media/blog/\">Read our blog</a> for meditation inspiration and reading plans.\r\n<h3>Sermons</h3>\r\nVisit our sermon archive at <a href=\"http://www.pointchurchsermons.com\">pointchurchsermons.com</a>.\r\n<h3>App</h3>\r\nDownload our <a href=\"https://a3a.me/point\">Point Church App</a>.\r\n<h3>Videos</h3>\r\nAll of our videos are hosted on <a href=\"https://vimeo.com/churchpoint\">our Vimeo profile</a>.\r\n<h3>Music</h3>\r\nTo listen to the songs we sing on Sundays check out our <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/user/pointworship\">Spotify Playlist</a>.\r\n<h3>Curriculum</h3>\r\nTo download the latest curriculum, <a href=\"http://www.pointchurch.com/media/curriculum/\">visit our curriculum page</a>.\r\n<h3>Annual Report</h3>\r\nTo view this past year\'s Annual Report, <a href=\"http://localhost:8000/media/annual-report/\">click here</a>.\r\n<h3>Facilities Request</h3>\r\nWould you like¬†to use our space? <a href=\"https://point.ccbchurch.com/w_form_response.php?form_id=86\">Fill out this online form</a>.', 'Media', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '12-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-02-22 10:31:46', '2017-02-22 15:31:46', '', 12, 'http://localhost:8000/2017/02/22/12-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(992, 4, '2017-02-22 14:49:17', '2017-02-22 19:49:17', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"Peter said to them, \'Repent, and each of you be baptized in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins; and you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit. For the promise is for you and your children and for all who are far off, as many as the Lord our God will call to Himself.‚Äô‚Äù ‚Äî Acts 2:38-39\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nRepent. Be Baptized. Receive the Holy Spirit‚Ä¶ Everyone.\r\n\r\nI love the series of events happening in these two verses, which culminate with the promised gift of the Holy Spirit, which is the Lord dwelling inside of us.\r\n\r\nRepent is the first response, turning from our ways and turning towards the Lord. It is a heart change and a redirection of our lives.\r\n\r\nBaptism follows repentance. How beautiful is it that we choose to follow the Lord? How beautiful is it that we are not forced to follow the Lord but it is a choice in each one of our lives. Baptism is an outward sign of an inward faith. We are professing and confessing that Christ is Lord, which means we off surrendering every single part of our lives to Him.\r\n\r\nBaptism, that first step of getting in the water, only happens once. The act of repentance and surrendering my life to the Lord happens over and over again, day after day, mistake after mistake.\r\n\r\nI receive the Holy Spirit then I have the choice whether or not I want to listen.\r\n\r\nThese are all hard things: to constantly come back to the Lord, to be humbled, to admit that I fail short on my own, and that I need a savior. I was never meant to save myself; God died for me so that I didn‚Äôt have to.\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nOur response to repentance is either baptism and surrender, both of which lead to life change.\r\n\r\nI was baptized my senior year of high school but I have the honor of sharing the life changing good news of the gospel every single day with students and those far from the Lord. So, my application of these verses is to never forget that I need to repent and respond to sin every single day. The Lord has always been working in my life, guiding me and pointing me to something bigger than myself.\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nLord I pray that you continue to guide me into your presence, that there is opportunity after opportunity for me to learn. Lord give me opportunities to share this Good News with others.', 'Promise #3 ‚Äì Salvation', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-3-salvation', '', '', '2017-02-23 10:30:58', '2017-02-23 15:30:58', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=992', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(994, 4, '2017-02-23 10:34:13', '2017-02-23 15:34:13', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"10 He does not deal with us according to our sins, nor repay us according to our iniquities. 11 For as high as the heavens are above the earth, so great is his steadfast love toward those who fear him; 12 as far as the east is from the west, so far does he remove our transgressions from us.‚Äù ‚Äî Psalm 103:10-12\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nPsalm 103 is a song of David where he sings about the great character qualities of God and His many wonderful works. God is merciful (v.10) and does not give us the punishment we deserve for our sins. His mercy is driven by His steadfast love (v.11) and His compassionate heart (v.13). It is amazing that his great love for us knows no bounds and that His <strong>forgiveness</strong> is perfect. He takes away our sins ‚Äì as far away as the east is from the west ‚Äì that‚Äôs GONE. God even has the capacity to remember my sins no more, ‚ÄúI, even I, am he who blots out your transgressions, for my own sake, and remembers your sins no more.‚Äù (Isaiah 43:25). Fearing God (v.11 &amp; 13), acknowledging who He is and responding to Him, is the critical element in experiencing his forgiveness and compassion.\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nWe sin against God through the wrong things we do, think or say. We also have sins of omission when we don‚Äôt do the things we should. ‚ÄúSo whoever knows the right thing to do and fails to do it, for him it is sin.‚Äù (James 4:17). Most of us commit dozens of sin everyday. Satan often uses the guilt &amp; shame from our sins to wreck our relationships, destroy our dreams and sabotage our service. God can drive our sins away and remember them no more. Once we have repented from our sins and asked for His forgiveness from them, why should we ever be burdened by them again? God is able to deliver on His promises, and forgiveness is one that we must experience to walk in the freedom He wants us to have. We must remember this.\r\n\r\nBecause of His greatness, God is able to forgive all sins, and He has displayed this over and over and over in Scripture. He forgave Moses of his murder, David for his adultery and murder, Saul for his rabid persecution of the church and more. Yes, there were consequences for their sins and there will be for ours. But, what would have happened if these guys had carried the burden of their shame &amp; guilt and never experienced the forgiveness of God? These men would have totally missed out on their adventures, experiences and fulfillment with God. Theirs are good examples for us to follow. Also, isn‚Äôt it wonderful to know that God used ‚Äúpeople with a past‚Äù to be a part of His great plans for mankind ‚Äì and that He still does that today!\r\n\r\nWhen we become followers of Jesus, we are forgiven of all of our sins and become saints (Ephesians 1:1), new creations (II Corinthians 5:17), ambassadors for Christ (II Corinthians 5:20) and children of God. ‚ÄúBut to all who did receive him, who believed in his name, he gave the right to become children of God...‚Äù John 1:12. As we come to understand our identity in Christ and follow Him, our lives will be characterized more by righteousness, and sin will become the exception rather than the rule for us. As believers, when we do sin, that does not break our relationship with God (we are still His children), but it does disrupt our fellowship with Him. That is why seeking forgiveness daily is so important ‚Äì to keep our fellowship with God close and pure. ‚ÄúIf we confess our sins, he is faithful and just and will forgive us our sins and purify us from all unrighteousness. (I John 1:9). YAY GOD!\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, I can only comprehend parts of your great forgiveness, but I do understand that is an overflow of who You are. I was a sinner, but through your great love, grace and forgiveness, I‚Äôm now a new creation, an ambassador of Christ and a saint ‚Äì no matter what the devil or others may say.\r\n\r\nLord, when Satan, the accuser, wants to bring up my past failures to weigh me down, to quench my passion or to distract me from following you, help me to remember that your forgiveness is real and complete as soon as I confess and repent.\r\n\r\nThank you God for sending Jesus to pay the penalty for my sins on the cross so that I could be forgiven. This shows me that you hate my sin, which separates us from you; but, more so, you value me and love me with a steadfast love that only You have.\r\n\r\nAs David prayed in Psalm 51 following his sins with Bathsheba, ‚ÄúCreate in me a clean heart O God and renew a right spirit within me‚Ä¶Restore to me the joy of your salvation and uphold me with a willing spirit.‚Äù Thank you for freedom from the penalty &amp; power of sin in my life.\r\nJesus as you so beautifully displayed love, compassion and forgiveness throughout your earthly ministry, fill me with your Spirit (Luke 11:13), that I might do the same.', 'Promise #4 ‚Äì Forgiveness', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-3-forgiveness', '', '', '2017-02-23 10:35:08', '2017-02-23 15:35:08', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=994', 0, 'post', '', 0);
