(996, 4, '2017-02-24 15:19:26', '2017-02-24 20:19:26', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"Jesus speaking to His disciples: ‚ÄúAs the Father has loved me, so have I loved you. Now remain in my love‚Äù ‚Äî John 15:9\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nMuch of Jesus‚Äô teaching comes through ‚Äúparables.‚Äù That means He put one common, easily understood idea beside a more abstract or less understood idea to help explain the latter. In a similar way in this passage Jesus uses an extended metaphor to put a common idea‚Äîvine, branches, and bearing fruit‚Äîbeside the more abstract idea of abiding in Him. In His day, everyone would know about vines and branches, roots and fruits. They would clearly understand the need for a branch to remain connected to the main part of the vine, in order to live and bear fruit. Therefore, Jesus makes the connection that His followers must abide in, or stay connected with, the True Vine, their Lord and Teacher, Jesus Christ. Apart from Him they could not live and certainly could not bear fruit. The same would be true of enjoying the blessings of God‚Äôs love for His people. Remaining in close relationship with Jesus, His disciples experience the rich blessings of His love (forgiveness, mercy and grace, too). And by abiding in Him they would bear much fruit, ‚Äúfruit that will last‚Äù (John 15:16).\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nI am no different than the followers of Jesus in His day. If I choose to follow Him and desire to enjoy His lavish love and rich blessings, I must remain connected to Him. During seasons of trial and the challenges of life, I experience true life, life to its fullest extent, as I continue to live in close relationship with God. Personally, when my father committed suicide many years ago, I chose to trust Jesus as my Lord and Savior and began to experience life and love as never before. When my family and I lived and served in Indonesia, we learned to walk in close fellowship with our Lord. And now, we have experienced many challenges with our move to Fuquay-Varina to plant a new Point Church here and to lead the church planting efforts for the Point. We choose daily to walk in faith, submitting to God‚Äôs call to be here, and He carries us through the challenges of finding a home, a location for the church to meet, finances, and starting all over again at our stage of life. But God is faithful. His steadfast love abides forever!\r\n\r\nBecause of His greatness, God is able to forgive all sins, and He has displayed this over and over and over in Scripture. He forgave Moses of his murder, David for his adultery and murder, Saul for his rabid persecution of the church and more. Yes, there were consequences for their sins and there will be for ours. But, what would have happened if these guys had carried the burden of their shame &amp; guilt and never experienced the forgiveness of God? These men would have totally missed out on their adventures, experiences and fulfillment with God. Theirs are good examples for us to follow. Also, isn‚Äôt it wonderful to know that God used ‚Äúpeople with a past‚Äù to be a part of His great plans for mankind ‚Äì and that He still does that today!\r\n\r\nWhen we become followers of Jesus, we are forgiven of all of our sins and become saints (Ephesians 1:1), new creations (II Corinthians 5:17), ambassadors for Christ (II Corinthians 5:20) and children of God. ‚ÄúBut to all who did receive him, who believed in his name, he gave the right to become children of God...‚Äù John 1:12. As we come to understand our identity in Christ and follow Him, our lives will be characterized more by righteousness, and sin will become the exception rather than the rule for us. As believers, when we do sin, that does not break our relationship with God (we are still His children), but it does disrupt our fellowship with Him. That is why seeking forgiveness daily is so important ‚Äì to keep our fellowship with God close and pure. ‚ÄúIf we confess our sins, he is faithful and just and will forgive us our sins and purify us from all unrighteousness. (I John 1:9). YAY GOD!\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nDear Lord, help me to live in close communion with you each and every day. When life‚Äôs challenges come my way, may I learn to lean closer into my relationship with You rather than pulling away. May You be honored in and through my life, more so through the trials than when all seems to be going well. Help me to use my experiences of difficult times to demonstrate Your love to everyone around me. In Your name I pray, Amen!', 'Promise #5 - Love', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-5-love', '', '', '2017-02-24 15:19:50', '2017-02-24 20:19:50', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=996', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(997, 4, '2017-02-24 15:19:29', '2017-02-24 20:19:29', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"Jesus speaking to His disciples: ‚ÄúAs the Father has loved me, so have I loved you. Now remain in my love‚Äù ‚Äî John 15:9\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nMuch of Jesus‚Äô teaching comes through ‚Äúparables.‚Äù That means He put one common, easily understood idea beside a more abstract or less understood idea to help explain the latter. In a similar way in this passage Jesus uses an extended metaphor to put a common idea‚Äîvine, branches, and bearing fruit‚Äîbeside the more abstract idea of abiding in Him. In His day, everyone would know about vines and branches, roots and fruits. They would clearly understand the need for a branch to remain connected to the main part of the vine, in order to live and bear fruit. Therefore, Jesus makes the connection that His followers must abide in, or stay connected with, the True Vine, their Lord and Teacher, Jesus Christ. Apart from Him they could not live and certainly could not bear fruit. The same would be true of enjoying the blessings of God‚Äôs love for His people. Remaining in close relationship with Jesus, His disciples experience the rich blessings of His love (forgiveness, mercy and grace, too). And by abiding in Him they would bear much fruit, ‚Äúfruit that will last‚Äù (John 15:16).\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nI am no different than the followers of Jesus in His day. If I choose to follow Him and desire to enjoy His lavish love and rich blessings, I must remain connected to Him. During seasons of trial and the challenges of life, I experience true life, life to its fullest extent, as I continue to live in close relationship with God. Personally, when my father committed suicide many years ago, I chose to trust Jesus as my Lord and Savior and began to experience life and love as never before. When my family and I lived and served in Indonesia, we learned to walk in close fellowship with our Lord. And now, we have experienced many challenges with our move to Fuquay-Varina to plant a new Point Church here and to lead the church planting efforts for the Point. We choose daily to walk in faith, submitting to God‚Äôs call to be here, and He carries us through the challenges of finding a home, a location for the church to meet, finances, and starting all over again at our stage of life. But God is faithful. His steadfast love abides forever!\r\n\r\nBecause of His greatness, God is able to forgive all sins, and He has displayed this over and over and over in Scripture. He forgave Moses of his murder, David for his adultery and murder, Saul for his rabid persecution of the church and more. Yes, there were consequences for their sins and there will be for ours. But, what would have happened if these guys had carried the burden of their shame &amp; guilt and never experienced the forgiveness of God? These men would have totally missed out on their adventures, experiences and fulfillment with God. Theirs are good examples for us to follow. Also, isn‚Äôt it wonderful to know that God used ‚Äúpeople with a past‚Äù to be a part of His great plans for mankind ‚Äì and that He still does that today!\r\n\r\nWhen we become followers of Jesus, we are forgiven of all of our sins and become saints (Ephesians 1:1), new creations (II Corinthians 5:17), ambassadors for Christ (II Corinthians 5:20) and children of God. ‚ÄúBut to all who did receive him, who believed in his name, he gave the right to become children of God...‚Äù John 1:12. As we come to understand our identity in Christ and follow Him, our lives will be characterized more by righteousness, and sin will become the exception rather than the rule for us. As believers, when we do sin, that does not break our relationship with God (we are still His children), but it does disrupt our fellowship with Him. That is why seeking forgiveness daily is so important ‚Äì to keep our fellowship with God close and pure. ‚ÄúIf we confess our sins, he is faithful and just and will forgive us our sins and purify us from all unrighteousness. (I John 1:9). YAY GOD!\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nDear Lord, help me to live in close communion with you each and every day. When life‚Äôs challenges come my way, may I learn to lean closer into my relationship with You rather than pulling away. May You be honored in and through my life, more so through the trials than when all seems to be going well. Help me to use my experiences of difficult times to demonstrate Your love to everyone around me. In Your name I pray, Amen!', 'Promise #5 - Love', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '996-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-02-24 15:19:29', '2017-02-24 20:19:29', '', 996, 'http://localhost:8000/2017/02/24/996-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(999, 4, '2017-02-27 08:44:36', '2017-02-27 13:44:36', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"Therefore, there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus‚Äù ‚Äî Romans 8:1\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nBecause of what Jesus has done for me, I am not condemned. I once was, but now I\'m not. Condemnation is a thing of the past for me. It is not a part of my present, and it will not be a part of my future. To live like I\'m condemned is to accept a lie, instead of embracing a truth.\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nI am good at condemning myself. I can be guilty of embracing Satan\'s view of me, instead of God\'s view of me. I need to discipline myself to daily reminding myself of the truth. I AM NOT CONDEMNED. I am a forgiven child of God. \r\n\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, thank you for forgiving me. Thank you for saving me. Help me to understand your grace. I can\'t fathom it sometimes, and as a result, I fail to live in it. In you Jesus, I am not condemned. Imprint that truth in my heart and mind today Jesus. Amen. ', 'Promise #6 - Guilt', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-6-guilt', '', '', '2017-02-27 08:44:36', '2017-02-27 13:44:36', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=999', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1001, 4, '2017-02-27 08:45:55', '2017-02-27 13:45:55', '', 'Keep_Calm_and_Carry_On_-_Week_2_-_Curriculum', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'keep_calm_and_carry_on_-_week_2_-_curriculum', '', '', '2017-02-27 08:45:55', '2017-02-27 13:45:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Keep_Calm_and_Carry_On_-_Week_2_-_Curriculum.pdf', 0, 'attachment', 'application/pdf', 0),
(1002, 4, '2017-02-28 10:15:01', '2017-02-28 15:15:01', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"See what kind of love the Father has given to us, that we should be called children of God; and so we are. The reason why the world does not know us is that it did not know him.‚Äù  - 1 John 3:1\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nOne of the ways God has demonstrated his love for us is by adopting us as his sons and daughters. This is our new identity. This new identity also gives a partial explanation as to why we experience struggles in this world: we are children of God, identified with Jesus, and at enmity with the prince of this world.\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nThe God of the universe calls you son/daughter. The same God that spoke this world into existence calls you a child of him. You are a prince/princess of the most high king. Live it. Know it. Bathe in it every morning. Use it as ammunition when this world is cruel, it did not know him, your king, of course it will be cruel to you...but take heart, your king has overcome this world.\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, you are not like an Earthly father. You are constant, ever-loving, all-knowing, and encouraging. You are my dad and I am your son. When you look at me you do not see failure. You do not see mistake. You see a son with whom you are well-pleased. A son you have chosen. A son worth the sacrifice of Jesus. Father, help that truth travel to my heart and never leave. Help me rest in my identity as your child. Today, let good works and performance flow from my given identity as your son. Today, let me see my hardships and struggles through a heavenly perspective. Amen.', 'Promise #7 - Identity', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-7-identity', '', '', '2017-02-28 10:15:01', '2017-02-28 15:15:01', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1002', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1004, 4, '2017-03-01 09:40:03', '2017-03-01 14:40:03', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"Those who know your name trust in you, for you, Lord, have never forsaken those who seek you.‚Äù     ‚Äî  Psalms 9:10\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nThe Psalmist paints for us a picture of what it looks like to trust in the Lord. The Psalmist tells us that we must know the Lord: who he is and what he is like; and if we do this we will trust in the Lord, because he has a perfect track record. He is steadfast, he is not a moving target to those that seek Him, and he promises that he will not forsake those that do seek him. The Lord is trustworthy because it is a part of his character.\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nWe can apply this beautiful truth to our lives, knowing that God is not like others. Even though friends and family generally have good intentions, they are not God and they can fail us and even forsake us in times of need. We must not only come to know that God has unfailing love for us, we must trust in the steadfastness of his love because it never changes. Man may fail us, but God\'s love for those that seek him never does.\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nLord help us to understand who you are not by how we or others are, but let us understand who you are by how you have revealed yourself. You are not like us; you do not change with the shifting winds; rather, you are a rock and an anchor for those who place there trust in you. Help us to remember your promise to never leave us nor forsake us.', 'Promise #8 - Steadfast', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-8-steadfast', '', '', '2017-03-01 09:40:03', '2017-03-01 14:40:03', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1004', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1008, 4, '2017-03-02 14:56:36', '2017-03-02 19:56:36', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"But this I call to mind, and therefore I have hope; The steadfast love of the Lord never ceases; his mercies never come to an end; they are new every morning; great is your faithfulness. \'The Lord is my portion,\' says my soul, \'therefore I will hope in him.\' The Lord is good to those who wait for him, to the soul who seeks him. It is good that one should wait quietly for the salvation of the Lord.\"  ‚Äî  Lamentations 3:21-26\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nThe author of this passage is in a pretty rough situation, and his circumstances seem dire, yet he knows that he must \"call to mind\" the things he knows about the Lord. Even though he\'s confident in the Lord\'s provision in his life, he has to remind himself. His hope is refreshed because he takes the time to remind himself about God\'s love, mercy, and faithfulness. He knows that God provides EVERY day, and that there is no end to that provision, but it\'s still something that he has to make an effort to remember and count on. He knows that the Lord will be faithful to provide, he just has to remind himself to wait patiently. \r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nWhen I take the time to read scripture and to look back on the things God has done in my life, I am reminded of His love, mercy, and faithfulness as well. My problem is that often times I get so caugt up in the circumstances and challenges of my life that I forget to take that time. I forget to \"call to mind\" my knowledge of who the Lord is and how He acts, which leads me to lose hope and try to solve things on my own. In order to really rely on the promise that \"The Lord is my portion,\" I need to take time to remember how He\'s acted in my life before and allow that to be my foundation for hope in my current circumstances. \r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nLord, thank you for the fact that you are my portion and your love, mercy, and faithfulness are not limited. I\'m sorry that I forget that so often. Please help me to be disciplined to spend time daily soaking up your word and reflecting on your goodness so that when trying circumstances come, I\'ll be able to easily remember your love, mercy, and faithfulness. Give me the confidence to rely on you alone as my portion and source of hope, regardless of circumstances. In Jesus\' name, Amen.  \r\n', 'Promise #9 - Sufficiency', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-9-guilt', '', '', '2017-03-02 14:57:23', '2017-03-02 19:57:23', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1008', 0, 'post', '', 0),
