(1013, 4, '2017-03-03 09:45:41', '2017-03-03 14:45:41', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"For nothing will be impossible with God.‚Äù ‚Äî Luke 1:37\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nThis is an angelic declaration, and so it has come from God. The celestial messengers, or angels (in this case Gabriel), do not speak on their own accord. As a direct message from God, this affirmation has the objective of affirming the soul, mind, and heart of Mary: just as her relative Elizabeth was pregnant, even though she was barren, in the same way Mary would have a baby without having been with any man. In this, we see the power of the Almighty coming upon an earthly family with the goal of showing us where our faith should be placed: in God. Our trust must be placed in His power, which consists on this: Nothing is impossible for Him.  If God makes this categoric affirmation it is because it is essential for future generations to come to place their faith in Him.  Our faith is not in religious duty or effort, but rather a personal God who has established the way in which He seeks us with His love.  We have the certainty that through His power, His love has no barriers of any kind, neither human nor spiritual. \r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nBy faith I will encompass, in the way I live my life, an affirmation that in every moment His Power is there for me.  In other words: no decision, no matter how simple or complex it may be, should be outside of my trust in His Power.  Because He has all the power, I will not trust in my own strength or talents, I will not feel independent from Him in anything and for no one.  My trust, then, in all that I do, comes from His direction and provision.  My goal in all that I set forth for myself is to grow the Kingdom of God, because I depend on Him, my eternal Father, and without a doubt: He can do all things as his power works in me, through me, and around me.\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nBlessed Lord, let me live by the revelation of Your Word and the presence of Your Holy Spirit in me.  Let me know without a doubt that all the purposes and designs You have for me will come to pass, even if they seem impossible in the earthly realm.  I will remember over and over again that NOTHING is impossible for You, my God, because you are the Almighty. In Christ, Amen.', 'Promise #10 - Power', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-10-power', '', '', '2017-03-03 09:45:41', '2017-03-03 14:45:41', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1013', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1015, 4, '2017-03-06 10:15:39', '2017-03-06 15:15:39', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\nThe Lord himself goes before you and will be with you; he will never leave you nor forsake you. Do not be afraid; do not be discouraged.‚Äù ‚Äî Deuteronomy 31:8\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nIn the midst of a potentially fearful time, these words are a comforting promise for the people of God. Moses is on the verge of death. The people are on the verge of taking the promised land. Joshua is on the verge of filling the huge shoes of Moses. All of these transitions create the potential of fear for the people of God. However, this promise of God‚Äôs presence provided Joshua and the people with what they needed to keep calm and carry on.\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nGod‚Äôs presence is what I need to keep calm and carry on. No matter the circumstances, even if they should invoke fear, he goes before me, he is with me, and he will never leave me. I have no reason to fear. If the God of the universe is with me, then I have no reason to be discouraged! There are no circumstances bigger than he is.\r\n\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nLord, thank you for surpassing all of my circumstances...even ones that threaten to discourage me. Thank you for your promise to be with me. I rest in your promise today. In Jesus name, amen.\r\n', 'Promise #11 - Presence', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-11-seek-find', '', '', '2017-03-07 09:06:06', '2017-03-07 14:06:06', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1015', 0, 'post', '', 0),
