(1020, 4, '2017-03-07 09:08:13', '2017-03-07 14:08:13', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"You will seek me and find me, when you seek me with all your heart.‚Äù ‚Äî Jeremiah 29:13\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nThe promises of God are true and everlasting. He promised to his chosen people that he would be their lord and their provider; that he would be their father and care for them. And here in this verse, we see that he continues His promise with the fact that He will always be found. He will be found by his people when they seek him with no reservations - with all of our heart, mind and strength.\r\n\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nGod does not have to be sought because he moves around like the game of hide and seek. It is us who lose sight of following him. We, like a child in a store, are drawn to something . . . like candy or a toy . . . money or fame. And we lose sight of the parent who just went around the corner to the next isle. Or we are like Jonah, who didn\'t like what our father asked us to do, and we run and hide from him, thinking He\'ll forget about it. \r\nHe never forgets and he always fulfills His promises! And He promises us, like He did the children of Israel, if you seek Me, I will Be Found!\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, may we not lose sight of you because we are striving for our own gain. May we strive to always be in your presence, for there is refuge, strength and supply for our day. Guide our eyes to be fixed upon You, our heart to be in sync with Yours, and strengthen our feet to keep up with you. This is our prayer to You. Amen.\r\n', 'Promise #12 - Seek & Find', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-12-seek-find', '', '', '2017-03-07 09:08:13', '2017-03-07 14:08:13', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1020', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1021, 4, '2017-03-07 09:08:20', '2017-03-07 14:08:20', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"You will seek me and find me, when you seek me with all your heart.‚Äù ‚Äî Jeremiah 29:13\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nThe promises of God are true and everlasting. He promised to his chosen people that he would be their lord and their provider; that he would be their father and care for them. And here in this verse, we see that he continues His promise with the fact that He will always be found. He will be found by his people when they seek him with no reservations - with all of our heart, mind and strength.\r\n\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nGod does not have to be sought because he moves around like the game of hide and seek. It is us who lose sight of following him. We, like a child in a store, are drawn to something . . . like candy or a toy . . . money or fame. And we lose sight of the parent who just went around the corner to the next isle. Or we are like Jonah, who didn\'t like what our father asked us to do, and we run and hide from him, thinking He\'ll forget about it. \r\nHe never forgets and he always fulfills His promises! And He promises us, like He did the children of Israel, if you seek Me, I will Be Found!\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, may we not lose sight of you because we are striving for our own gain. May we strive to always be in your presence, for there is refuge, strength and supply for our day. Guide our eyes to be fixed upon You, our heart to be in sync with Yours, and strengthen our feet to keep up with you. This is our prayer to You. Amen.\r\n', 'Promise #12 - Seek & Find', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1020-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-03-07 09:08:20', '2017-03-07 14:08:20', '', 1020, 'http://localhost:8000/2017/03/07/1020-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1022, 4, '2017-03-08 08:11:08', '2017-03-08 13:11:08', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"And the gospel must first be preached to all the nations.‚Äù ‚Äî Mark 13:10\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nIn this passage, Jesus has returned to Jerusalem one last time.  He has been busy teaching his disciples and being tested by the religious leaders.  He has just told his disciples the temple would be destroyed, and, when they were alone, they asked him when and how it would happen. In Mark‚Äôs gospel, he doesn‚Äôt actually answer them, but rather talks about the time leading up to when he will return as the Lion, saving his allies, and destroying his enemies.  In the middle of this teaching, he gives a preliminary condition for any of this happening--the gospel must first be preached to all nations.  The word ‚Äúnation\" doesn‚Äôt mean countries as I one typically understands it, rather it means \"people groups.\"  A people group has their own unique language and culture.  He sent them to the WHOLE world, and it took them until after he was gone . . . and then some . . . to understand it.\r\n\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nI am also sent to participate in the events leading to Jesus‚Äô return.  There are more than 1,700 unreached people groups in the countries of South Asia alone.  That means more than one billion people have never even had a chance to hear about Jesus.  If I want Christ to return, I must go.  There are many reasons to go to India for the cause of Christ, but to aid in his return is a powerful one.  Jesus has given me, . . . . give all of us . . . a job to do. How dare we disobey.\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nJesus, come quickly.  Thank you for your patience with me as I regularly fail to participate in your plan for the nations.  Forgive me for fearing to go to the unreached peoples of the world.  Give me the courage to participate in your return by going to India and sharing you with others in that nation.  You are worth ALL the risk.  I love you Jesus. Amen.', 'Promise #13 - Prayer', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-13-prayer', '', '', '2017-03-08 08:11:08', '2017-03-08 13:11:08', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1022', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1023, 4, '2017-03-09 16:52:05', '2017-03-09 21:52:05', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"And we know that in all things God works for the good of those who love him, who have been called according to his purpose.‚Äù ‚Äî Romans 8:28\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nGod works through everything for both our good and His glory. In the following verse, Paul further explains that this process involves God conforming us into the likeness of his son. Therefore it is for our good to allow God to use all things to mold is into the image of Christ. And the more Christ-like we become, the more we will fulfill God\'s purpose for our lives.\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nOften, the process of becoming more Christ-like is painful and humbling. God sometimes uses very difficult situations to change our hearts. But I\'m reminded of the agonizing and humiliating process Jesus went through so that we might become God\'s children! Every bit of his suffering was necessary and according to God\'s perfect plan to bring salvation to the world! And Jesus entered that suffering willingly, knowing that his Father\'s plan was good. I also must trust that God is working everything for my good even if it doesn\'t feel good all the time. And in the darkest and most difficult periods of my life, I must trust that my loving Father is perfectly at work.\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nLord, I give you permission to use whatever means necessary to form me into the likeness of your son. Remove all the areas of my life that are displeasing to you and help me to reflect the glory of Christ so that I can fulfill your purpose for my life. Thank you for working all things out for my good and your glory! Amen.', 'Promise #14 - Goodness', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-14-goodness', '', '', '2017-03-09 16:52:05', '2017-03-09 21:52:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1023', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1024, 4, '2017-03-08 08:11:28', '2017-03-08 13:11:28', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"And the gospel must first be preached to all the nations.‚Äù ‚Äî Mark 13:10\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nIn this passage, Jesus has returned to Jerusalem one last time.  He has been busy teaching his disciples and being tested by the religious leaders.  He has just told his disciples the temple would be destroyed, and, when they were alone, they asked him when and how it would happen. In Mark‚Äôs gospel, he doesn‚Äôt actually answer them, but rather talks about the time leading up to when he will return as the Lion, saving his allies, and destroying his enemies.  In the middle of this teaching, he gives a preliminary condition for any of this happening--the gospel must first be preached to all nations.  The word ‚Äúnation\" doesn‚Äôt mean countries as I one typically understands it, rather it means \"people groups.\"  A people group has their own unique language and culture.  He sent them to the WHOLE world, and it took them until after he was gone . . . and then some . . . to understand it.\r\n\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nI am also sent to participate in the events leading to Jesus‚Äô return.  There are more than 1,700 unreached people groups in the countries of South Asia alone.  That means more than one billion people have never even had a chance to hear about Jesus.  If I want Christ to return, I must go.  There are many reasons to go to India for the cause of Christ, but to aid in his return is a powerful one.  Jesus has given me, . . . . give all of us . . . a job to do. How dare we disobey.\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nJesus, come quickly.  Thank you for your patience with me as I regularly fail to participate in your plan for the nations.  Forgive me for fearing to go to the unreached peoples of the world.  Give me the courage to participate in your return by going to India and sharing you with others in that nation.  You are worth ALL the risk.  I love you Jesus. Amen.', 'Promise #13 - Prayer', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1022-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-03-08 08:11:28', '2017-03-08 13:11:28', '', 1022, 'http://localhost:8000/2017/03/08/1022-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1026, 3, '2017-03-09 09:48:08', '2017-03-09 14:48:08', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><em><span style=\"color: #00a0c6;\">\"For the earth will be filled with the knowledge of the glory of the Lord as the waters cover the sea.\"</span></em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #00a0c6;\">- Habakkuk 2:14</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdzyujNLYgZ8H5_lF_tbjsABJQw82Zotu92XMJrEf6s0oYKvA/viewform\">Apply Here Today!</a></strong></p>\n\n<h3>United States</h3>\nEvery year we partner the Carolina Movement our church planting coaltion to help plant a new church in the United States, specifically North Carolina. ¬†Each fall we take a weekend mission trip to help the new church get off the ground.\n\nIn the past, we have worked with many church planting organizations to help churches across the USA. In 2013, we worked with Christ\'s Church Albany in Albany, NY, in 2014, we partnered with Canvas Church in Winchester, VA, and in 2015 we worked with Good News Church in Columbus, Ohio. In 2016, we went We took trips to both cities to do outreaches and provide volunteers for their weekend services.\n\nThis year, we will be traveling to Augusta, Georgia¬†from October 7 - 9¬†to help get <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Venture Church</span> up and running. The cost for this trip will be only $99. We would love for you to join us on this mission to spread God\'s love in Georgia!\n\nGo to <a href=\"http://localhost:8000/usa\">pointchurch.com/usa</a> for more information, and to sign up today!\n<h3>Dominican Republic</h3>\nWe partner with Rueben and Vicky Dominguez who started H.O.P.E. Dominican Republic. They are committed to bring Christ centered transformation to the Dominican Republic through church planting and meeting the needs of needy children. They have planted two churches and have opened a feeding and education center for 100 children. <a href=\"http://hope4drnow.org/\">Get more information here.</a>\n\nWe are now working with them to plant a church in Puerto Plata. We look forward to visiting this community on our next trip. Contact Elise at elise@pointchurch.com for more info!\n<h3>India</h3>\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Central India Christian Mission </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">is our partner in India. They respond to the needs of the people in central and northern India through church planting, medical care, disaster relief, and discipleship. They have planted more than 1400 churches and baptized more than 400,000 people. With CICM we are working in Northern India¬†to plant churches and sponsor children in poverty.</span>\n\n<a href=\"https://indiamission.org/\">indiamission.org/</a>\n<h3>Middle East</h3>\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Canaan Project is located in a primarily Muslim Country in the Middle East and is focused on community development. It provides clean drinking water, technology centers, and schools for girls. The work is supported through a recognized NGO. One family from the church currently lives and works with this unreached people group. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Through CICM we are able to sponsor refugee children from this unreached people group. </span>\n\nTo get more involved with the Canaan Project email Chris Gregory at<b> <a href=\"mailto:drcg35@nc.rr.com\">drcg35@nc.rr.com</a>.</b>', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '108-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-03-09 09:48:08', '2017-03-09 14:48:08', '', 108, 'http://localhost:8000/2017/03/09/108-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1027, 3, '2017-03-09 09:58:43', '2017-03-09 14:58:43', 'We have a great opportunity to help <span class=\"il\">New</span> <span class=\"il\">City</span> <span class=\"il\">Church</span> (on 8515 Creedmore Road, Suite 101) prepare for their March launch. They are our next Level 1 - USA partner church. There are two ways we can help get them ready for their March 19 launch.\r\n\r\n1. PAINT THEIR FACILITY:\r\n<span class=\"il\">New</span> <span class=\"il\">City</span> <span class=\"il\">Church</span> is launching on Sunday, March 19, but they are doing a special event in the building <span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_1486893825\"><span class=\"aQJ\">on Friday the 17th</span></span>. ¬†Our goal is to help them finish the job by Wednesday night, <span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_1486893826\"><span class=\"aQJ\">March 15</span></span>. ¬†Charlie Soden will have lots of the paint supplies and the paint on site ready to go <span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_1486893827\"><span class=\"aQJ\">on Thursday</span></span> night. (Way to go Charlie!) If you want to bring an extra brush, it might come in handy. The facility was previously used by a <span class=\"il\">church</span> so the walls are in good shape and <span class=\"il\">New</span> <span class=\"il\">City</span> <span class=\"il\">Church</span> members have already taped the trim.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>PAINTING DAYS:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>March 14 - 6pm-9pm</li>\r\n 	<li>March 15 - 6pm -9pm</li>\r\n 	<li>Show up when you can, stay as long as you can, the whole time or part of it.</li>\r\n 	<li>Questions - Contact Chuck Thompson ‚Äì <a href=\"mailto:Chuckt@pointchurch.com\" target=\"_blank\">Chuckt@pointchurch.com</a> or <a href=\"tel:(919)%20602-5677\" target=\"_blank\">919-602-5677</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n2. SERVE ON SUNDAYS\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We want to help provide volunteers for New City Church on their first four Sunday