(1040, 1, '2017-03-12 10:44:17', '2017-03-12 15:44:17', '<h3>Need Food Assistance?</h3>\r\nThe Point¬†Food Pantry serves families in need of food assistance by providing a couple of bags of groceries, a hot meal, and clothing every <strong>Saturday from 11:00 am to 12:00 pm.</strong> Families must live in Wake County and arrive no earlier than 10am on Saturday mornings. Assistance is given on a first come, first served basis.\r\n<h4>The food pantry is located in three locations:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Cary:¬†<strong>1503 Walnut St, Cary NC</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Apex:¬†<strong>1402 E Williams St,¬†Apex NC</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>Raleigh:¬†<strong>3700 Lake Wheeler Rd, Raleigh NC</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nContact us at 919-467-9159.\r\n\r\nMembers of The Point Church are welcome to receive assistance on Fridays from 4:00 pm to 5:00 pm. Email Jensen at <a href=\"mailto:jensend@pointchurch.com\">jensend@pointchurch.com</a>¬†to make arrangements.\r\n<a name=\"volunteer\"></a>\r\n<h3>Want to Volunteer?</h3>\r\nThanks for your interest in serving at our Care Center! We have many opportunities available. You will likely be scheduled to serve only once in a month (unless you want to do more!). Please fill out <a href=\"http://localhost:8000/pageredir/785\">this¬†form</a>¬†so we can learn more about your interests and availability. Once you submit the form, someone from our Care Ministry team will follow up to speak with you further. We‚Äôre excited for what God is going to do through you in our Care Ministry!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Weekend Opportunities:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Care Center</strong>- Come serve as a volunteer or leader at one of our three Care Centers (South Raleigh, Apex, Cary). Our Care Centers are open from 11am-noon every Saturday. An array of different opportunities are available to fit your passions and skill set. Volunteers and leaders arrive at 9:30am and are normally done by 12:30pm. </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Data Entry</strong>- There are opportunities available to assist with data entry during the week. Often, this is done on Mondays at our Cary Campus but times can be flexible. </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Food Runners</strong>- These volunteers will use our box truck to transport the bags of food from our Apex storage area to our Cary and South Raleigh campuses on Saturday mornings. This can also be done any time on Fridays, depending on a volunteer team‚Äôs availability. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4>Weekday Opportunities:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Shoppers</strong>- We need shoppers to visit the Eastern NC Food Bank in Raleigh on Mondays. This role includes gathering needed food items at the Food Bank warehouse and transporting the products to our Apex and Cary locations. We are looking to build volunteer teams of 3-4 people. This is normally done on Mondays from 9am-12pm, however some Tuesdays may be required. Preferably, volunteers will be comfortable lifting up to 25lbs and driving a box truck. </span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Grocery Donation Pickup-</strong>¬†We are blessed to receive food donations from several area grocery stores! Pickup times vary but are normally on weekday mornings. </span></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Grocery Baggers</strong>- If you‚Äôve served with us on a Saturday, you‚Äôve seen the paper bags full of groceries we provide to our guests each week. We currently distribute nearly 400 bags each week! These bags are filled with products each Thursday evening from 6:30-8pm at our Apex Campus. We are looking to form teams of 7-8 volunteers. Each team will prepare grocery bags once a month.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nQuestions about The Point Care Pantry? Email Jensen Davis at jensend@pointchurch.com for more information.', 'Care Pantry', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '66-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-03-12 10:44:17', '2017-03-12 15:44:17', '', 66, 'http://localhost:8000/2017/03/12/66-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1041, 4, '2017-03-13 11:14:45', '2017-03-13 16:14:45', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n\"For we do not have a high priest who is unable to empathize with our weaknesses, but we have one who has been tempted in every way, just as we are‚Äîyet he did not sin. Let us then approach God‚Äôs throne of grace with confidence, so that we may receive mercy and find grace to help us in our time of need.‚Äù   ‚Äî Hebrews 4:15-16\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nUnlike any other god in any other religion, we worship and follow a god who came to earth, put on flesh and walked through our neighborhoods. What sets Jesus apart form the other gods this world has to offer, is that he is FULLY human. He understand the trials, temptations and weakness of humanity. And he is motivated towards his followers by love, which prompts him to offer mercy and grace to help us in our times of need . . . times when temptation to sinful disobedience seems overwhelming. What a God we worship!   \r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nWe all have been in relationships in which the person listening to us did not UNDERSTAND what we were going through . . . they had not experienced enough pain . . . they could not identify with our particular suffering . . . particularly when that suffering was the result of our own weakness. So, we walk away feeling less comforted and far more alone. Fortunately, we do not have a God who cannot empathize; rather, we have a great high priest in Jesus who understands the challenge we face in resisting temptation and waking in a new way of life. Since he has \'put on skin‚Äô and walked this earth, he not only knows the challenge, but he compassionately offers mercy and grace to help us walk in this new way of righteous obedience.\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, forgive me for where my sinful flesh has overwhelmed my weak heart. I need you to empower me through your Spirit to build the character to resist and flee the devil. Thank you for understanding and walking compassionately with me. Thank you for your grace and mercy.\r\n', 'Promise #16 - Understanding', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-16-understanding', '', '', '2017-03-13 11:14:45', '2017-03-13 16:14:45', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1041', 0, 'post', '', 0),
