(1045, 4, '2017-03-14 15:14:48', '2017-03-14 20:14:48', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúThe Lord is with me, I will not be afraid.  What can man do to me? The Lord is with me, He is my helper.  I will look in triumph on my enemies.‚Äù - Psalm 119:6-7\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nAs long as God is with you, you have nothing to fear!  The good news is that God promises to be with his people!  When God is with you, you can walk through the valley of the shadow of death and fear no evil (Ps. 23:4).  When God is with you, you can be strong and courageous (Josh 1:8-9).  Your enemies can do nothing to you and you will look in triumph over the powers of darkness!\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nI will fear no evil, for you are with me!  I will not be afraid.  The Lord is my help or and with his help we will triumph over the powers of darkness in the Triangle! \r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, I think you that you have put your Spirit inside of me so that I can be confident that you are always with me!  Help me to cling to this truth and be strong and courageous.  Not afraid or discouraged!  In Jesus Name, Amen. \r\n\r\n', 'Promise #17 - Fear', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-17-fear', '', '', '2017-03-14 15:17:11', '2017-03-14 20:17:11', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1045', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1047, 3, '2017-03-14 15:33:10', '2017-03-14 20:33:10', '<a href=\"http://localhost:8000/give\">GIVE ONLINE</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>What is ‚ÄúWhat If?‚Äù</h3>\nTwo years ago The Point Church family asked a ‚ÄúWhat if?‚Äù question. ‚ÄúWhat if we go ALL IN to point more people to Jesus than ever before?‚Äù We believed in faith that God might double the number of people we reach in Wake County. That‚Äôs exactly what happened! We‚Äôve gone from averaging 443 people in weekly attendance to 900. We‚Äôve also baptized over 150 people since the start of All In!\n\nWe are entering a new season of faith and expectancy called, ‚ÄúWhat If?‚Äù. What if God wants to do something miraculous in and through us again over the next two years?\n\nThe leadership of The Point Church is confident that He does. The ‚ÄúWhat If?‚Äùquestion this time is this: What if we could go from 6 to 10 healthy campuses over the next 2 years?\n<h3>Next Steps</h3>\nWe are asking you to go on a ‚ÄúWhat If?‚Äù journey with God and your family. What if you believed the promises of God were true in your life? We are asking you to live as if they are and take the biggest step of generosity you‚Äôve ever taken to accomplish all that God has for us.\n\nThere are 3 steps that we‚Äôre asking you to take:\n<ol>\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #00a0c6;\"><strong>Pray.</strong></span> Pray that God would show us what is possible if we believe His promises are true. Pray that He would do abundantly more than we ask or imagine to point people to Jesus</li>\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #00a0c6;\"><strong>Commit.</strong></span> Help us reach our goal of 100 percent participation in this life-changing experience. Stand side by side with your church family. Commit to do whatever God asks and put your ‚Äúyes‚Äù on the table.</li>\n 	<li><span style=\"color: #00a0c6;\"><strong>Give.</strong></span> Ask God to show you during this season what a sacrificial gift looks like, and take whatever bold steps are required to see it through.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3>Resources</h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/What-If-Booklet-small-1.pdf\">What If Guide Book</a></li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://point.ccbchurch.com/form_response.php?id=97\">Make a Commitment</a></li>\n 	<li><a href=\"http://localhost:8000/give/\">Give Online</a></li>\n</ul>', 'What If', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '742-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-03-14 15:33:10', '2017-03-14 20:33:10', '', 742, 'http://localhost:8000/2017/03/14/742-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1049, 4, '2017-03-15 10:22:10', '2017-03-15 15:22:10', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúBut he said to me, ‚ÄúMy grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness.‚Äù Therefore I will boast all the more gladly about my weaknesses, so that Christ‚Äôs power may rest on me.‚Äù ‚Äî 2 Corinthians 12:9\r\n\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nPaul has spent some time ‚Äúboasting‚Äù because it‚Äôs what the Corinthians understand.  Then he spends some time sharing about his weakness‚Ä¶ kinda.  I don‚Äôt know what his weakness is, but it‚Äôs something he wants to be taken away.  Is it something he wants gone from a pride standpoint?  He writes to the Corinthians about not being a trained speaker.  Is it a sin he struggles with?  Is it a physical disability that makes it difficult to travel to new cities and plant churches?  Poor eyesight?  I wish I knew what it was.\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nRegardless of the weakness Paul is describing, I‚Äôve experienced this same thing and I can understand where he is coming from.  I don‚Äôt like to be weak.  I want to be strong‚Ä¶ self-sufficient‚Ä¶ well respected‚Ä¶ liked by everyone.  But I‚Äôve learned the truth of this verse over the years.  I‚Äôve learned to not only accept when there is a weakness, but look for how God is going to use it.  To stop focusing on myself and start focusing on God.  This has not only happened personally, but taking place right now, as I am leading students on a missions trip in Philly for the week. As I look around at our present context I see so many areas where it seems impossible for good to happen.  I‚Äôm so thankful for this promise this week.  To know that in our weakness, there is space for God to work‚Ä¶ to make himself known.  I‚Äôm praying this so much for the different ministries I‚Äôm seeing at work in this city this week.\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, thank you for using me.  Thank you for being faithful.  I‚Äôm so thankful I don‚Äôt have to be perfect to be used by you.  So much of my life I have wanted to change who I was.  I wanted to be ‚Äúbetter.\" I wanted to be an extravert rather than an introvert.  I wanted to be the life of the party.  I wanted to have gifts and abilities I saw in others.  I doubted that you couldn‚Äôt use me as I am.  But over the years I‚Äôve realized that‚Äôs putting the focus on me.  But You are the focal point, not me.  You are the one who can save, not me.  You are the one who can do a great work in people, not me.  I just need to be faithful and available to be used by you.  God, thank you for sending a perfect message through imperfect people like me.  Through all my faults, it makes it obvious that it‚Äôs you and not me who is doing the work.  Thanks for allowing me to partner with you in your work.  And Father, I do pray for the different ministries spread over this city.  Remind them of who you are.  Help them to see hope when situations around them might seem hopeless.  Actually, help them to get excited because they should be expecting to see you move in those areas.  I pray they see your power move in mighty ways.  Help me to see you move in mighty ways as well.\r\n', 'Promise #18 - Weakness', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-18-weakness', '', '', '2017-03-15 10:22:10', '2017-03-15 15:22:10', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1049', 0, 'post', '', 0),
