(1054, 4, '2017-03-17 07:29:04', '2017-03-17 12:29:04', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúIf any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask God, who gives generously to all without reproach, and it will be given him.‚Äù ‚Äî James 1:5\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nJames, the half brother of Jesus, is writing to believers who are scattered due to persecution. I have always appreciated James\'s practical application of Christian faith. In this section of the letter he is talking mainly about trials and inserts this verse about wisdom. Certainly in trials I need wisdom: ‚ÄùWhat do I do now God?‚Äù ‚ÄúHow should I respond to this?‚Äù God answers these prayers generously. James later tells us in 3:17 what the wisdom of God is like. ‚ÄúBut the wisdom of God from above is first pure, then peaceable, gentle, open to reason, full of mercy and good fruit, impartial and sincere.‚Äù God gives wisdom without finding fault.\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nI can ask God for wisdom - and need to do so and should do so ‚Äì even when I am living at peace, and not just when I\'m undergoing stressful situations. James probably could have written, not ‚Äúif‚Äù anyone lacks wisdom but ‚Äúwhen‚Äù you lack wisdom, because it seems like the case for me ‚Äì a good deal of the time. Sometimes I, like so many others, seem to hold to statements like ‚ÄúWhy pray when you can worry?‚Äù rather than practicing ‚ÄúWhy worry, when you can pray and ask God for His wisdom in the midst of trials?‚Äù\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nThank you Lord for the promise to give me wisdom when I ask because I sure need it.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Lord, grant me wisdom on how to be a good husband, father and leader for my family.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Lord, grant me wisdom so that I can best coach, mentor, equip, and minister to those around me.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Lord, grant me wisdom and how to be the steward of my time so that I can make the most of it. Grant me wisdom in dealing with various interruptions and opportunities.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Lord, grant me wisdom to be a faithful steward of the financial resources that You have provided me ‚Äì help me maximize them.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Lord, grant me wisdom for Your direction of my ministry so that I will accomplish Your agenda. I don‚Äôt want to take the easy way out.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Lord, grant me wisdom in my interaction with others so that I can best represent You. I want to challenge &amp; inspire them in their devotion and service to you.\r\nWill grant me wisdom so that I can find rest and be renewed in the midst of a full schedule.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Lord, grant me wisdom in responding to questions that I do not have good answers for.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Lord, grant me Your wisdom, not earthly wisdom as I respond to various situations and questions where the ‚Äúwater is muddy‚Äù.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Lord, grant me wisdom to balance all of my responsibilities and keep a calm spirit.</p>', 'Promise #20 - Wisdom', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-20-wisdom', '', '', '2017-03-17 07:37:24', '2017-03-17 12:37:24', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1054', 0, 'post', '', 0),
