(1068, 4, '2017-03-21 09:13:01', '2017-03-21 14:13:01', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúBut when they arrest you, do not worry about what to say or how to say it. At that time you will be given what to say, for it will not be you speaking, but the Spirit of your Father speaking through you.\"	‚Äî Matthew 10:19-20\r\n\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nJesus was promising the disciples that they would be persecuted, and they would suffer. The would be brought before governors and kings. While we aren\'t promised that we will be brought before governors and kings, Jesus promises in John 16:33 that \"in this world we will have trouble.\" Words can be hard to articulate in normal circumstances. It is even harder to know what, or how, or when to say something when the going gets tough. The fear of not knowing what to say in any given circumstance is one of humanity\'s greatest fears. This promise of Jesus is the remedy. It is natural to fear not knowing what to say. It is supernatural to not fear, because you take Jesus at His word, and know that the Holy Spirit will give you the words to say.  \r\n\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\n I think this promise assumes that the disciples being referred to would be living a life \"walking by the spirit.\" If I am walking with the Spirit, I will experience the truth of this promise. In difficult times, I should be slow to speak, and quick to listen what the Holy Spirit is speaking to me, trusting that He will provide the words.\r\n\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, thank you that I don\'t have to fear knowing the right words to say when I need them. Jesus, you are the Word of God, and you promise to give me your words, through your Spirit, when I need them. Help me not rely on my own words, but to wait upon yours father. You are my provider. ', 'Promise #21 - Uncertainty', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-21-uncertainty', '', '', '2017-03-21 09:13:01', '2017-03-21 14:13:01', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1068', 0, 'post', '', 0),
