(1070, 4, '2017-03-21 09:19:14', '2017-03-21 14:19:14', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúTrust in the Lord with all your heart and lean not on your own understanding; in all your ways submit to him, and he will direct your paths.‚Äù  ‚Äî Proverbs 3:5-6\r\n\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nThese two verses are a part of the introductory section of the book of Proverbs. The first nine chapters summarize a father‚Äôs advice (i.e., warnings) to his young adult son to avoid the desires of this world, particularly as regards wayward women. In these verses the father urges his son to wholeheartedly trust in and submit to the Lord and don‚Äôt even begin to think he‚Äôs got it all figured out. The father knows all too well that his son will quickly stray from both his and the Lord‚Äôs guidance should he choose to follow his own foolish ways. But therein lays the rub! We all think we know best, especially when we are young.\r\n\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nThese are two power-packed verses. The Lord promises to guide our paths, but you and I must do three things: trust in Him, lean on Him, and submit to Him. These are not words our culture wants to hear. And, if I‚Äôm honest, my lips may say ‚ÄúYes I will!‚Äù but my actions far too often guide me along my own destructive paths. Trust is hard to come by these days, even in your ‚Äúbest friend,‚Äù much less someone you cannot see or touch. Yet, He wants me to trust Him with ‚Äúall my heart?!.\" That means no doubting, and no fingers-crossed-behind-my-back kind of promise on my part! Then we‚Äôre told to not even consider our uber-limited understanding . . . to act like I really do not know what‚Äôs best for me?! Okay, well, maybe not!? But, wait a minute!! You‚Äôre beginning to meddle! I‚Äôll try to trust the Lord and lean on His wisdom; but what about ‚Äúsubmission‚Äù?!?! Now that‚Äôs going too far! ___ Or is it! Which is the better path to take? Is it one that I think I can control with my limited knowledge and understanding? Or is it the one laid out for me by the All-Powerful, All-Knowing, All-Present and loving Lord and Creator of the universe?!\r\n\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, teach me how to trust in you with all that I am so that I will no longer think I know better. Help me to submit to Your guidance and Your ways as I follow Your direction for my life! Amen.', 'Promise #22 - Guidance', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-22-guidance', '', '', '2017-03-21 09:19:14', '2017-03-21 14:19:14', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1070', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1071, 4, '2017-03-22 10:42:27', '2017-03-22 15:42:27', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúSurely God is my help; the Lord is the one who sustains me.‚Äù ‚Äî Psalm 54:4\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nThere will be many times and places in my life that I will need outside help. There will be times that no matter how much my friends and family want to help, they will not be able to offer the help I need; it will have to come from God. The Psalmist is reminding me that God is and will be my help in my time of need - that I can count on him to be there for me.\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nWhether I am struggling or things are going good, I can remember where my help truly comes from, what truly sustains me, and that is God.\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nLord allow me to remember where my help comes from. Let me run to you first, not last, trusting that you alone can provide for me and you alone can sustain me. Teach me to learn more and more to depend on you and take comfort, knowing that you will always provide. Amen', 'Promise #23 - Protection', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-23-uncertainty', '', '', '2017-03-27 09:35:09', '2017-03-27 14:35:09', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1071', 0, 'post', '', 0),
