(1078, 4, '2017-03-23 08:27:28', '2017-03-23 13:27:28', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúAnd my God will meet all your needs according to the riches of his glory in Christ Jesus.\" - Philippians 4:19 (NIV)\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nPaul is writing to a group of people that had given to his ministry to the point that it hurt. The middle of Philippians 4 is his thank you note for their provision to his ministry and it ends with a promise from God. The God of the bible, the God of all creation, the God outside of time and space will meet ALL the needs of these Philippians. This means needs that they are worried about, needs that they are not worried about, and needs that they haven\'t even thought of yet...the God of the bible will meet ALL THEIR NEEDS. But wait, there\'s more! Not meet their needs according to themselves...according to their measure of goodness or obedience...instead in accordance to the riches of his glory in Christ Jesus. These people have worked to meet the needs of another (Paul), which created a need for themselves that God was going to meet according to the riches of his glory in Jesus.\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nCan you think of one time in your life when you have given of yourself (time, money, etc.) to meet the needs of another where God did not also meet your needs? Really take some time to think about it. Why would it be any different today? The promise still stands. Give of yourself today to others, for God, with freedom, in the full assurance that he will meet ALL of your needs.\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, help me make much of you today through the giving of myself to others. Help me give in freedom, with no anxiety or caution, knowing full-well that you are my provider. Please make me aware of my provision from you today so that I can learn to walk this life step by step with you. Please make me most aware of my eternal provision that was provided by your son. Let my life today bring glory and honor to his name. Amen.', 'Promise #24 - Provision', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-23-provision', '', '', '2017-03-27 09:35:49', '2017-03-27 14:35:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1078', 0, 'post', '', 0),
