(1100, 4, '2017-03-24 10:58:50', '2017-03-24 15:58:50', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúThe Lord will fight for you, and you have only to be silent.‚Äù Exodus 14:14 (ESV)\r\n\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nWhen we look at the verses prior to this one, we see a desperate people facing the imminent threat of the approaching Egyptian army with nothing but vengeance and destruction in their intentions.  They are witnesses to a column of fire during the night and a huge protective cloud during the day, a clear aid from God to help them during the cold of night and the overwhelming heat of the day.  Even then, they live so much in their own circumstances that this situation leads them to complain severely before Moses, claiming he had forced them out of Egypt, and even leading him to believe that they did not want to leave - something completely false.  In accusing Moses, it is evident they are accusing God himself.  Moses sees their fear and encourages them to trust in God.  He knows they can remain calm because God knows everything. \r\n\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nThe Israelites showed their disappointment as a direct result of their desperation.  It was evident that they were blinded by terror.  The chaos had taken over their minds and they were no longer thinking with clarity.  The phrase: ‚Äú.. it would have been better for us to serve the Egyptians than to die in the wilderness...‚Äù highlights the fatal contradictions in their unstable character and their hearts filled with fear.  I do not want to move in those dimensions of desperation.  I know that at any moment I could face a test, weather it is simple or complex, but for God the size of the anguish or the problem makes no difference.  He knows how I will carry on from that situation.  I need to learn to trust in my God completely.  Each day he provides me with a column of fire to keep me warm in the middle of my most intense fears.  He also provides me with a protective cloud, that keeps me safe from the inclement heat of this world‚Äôs passions.  I know He asks me to remain calm.  My goal is to do just that, because by the seal of the Holy Spirit, who is my defender and counselor, I have strength to overcome any force that wants to take away the unbreakable faith in my God.  \r\n\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nBlessed Lord, I pray in the name of Jesus and in the power of the Holy Spirit that I may live in peace.  I know this is not easy for me because my personality is impulsive.  Only your power and grace will grant me wisdom so that I do not let the stubbornness of my thoughts and emotions guide me.  Let me feel that you are my defender at all times.  You are my Advocate, and You know what I need even before I ask for it.  Thank you for your mercy. In Christ\'s name, Amen. ', 'Promise #25 - Defender', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-25-defender', '', '', '2017-03-28 09:56:24', '2017-03-28 14:56:24', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1100', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1101, 4, '2017-03-27 09:42:17', '2017-03-27 14:42:17', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúLittle children, you are from God and have overcome them, for he who is in you is greater than he who is in the world.‚Äù   ‚Äî 1 John 4:4 (ESV)\r\n\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nBeing \"from God\" refers to the fact that as believers, we are now considered children of God. That status gives us power beyond our own strength because we have the Holy Spirit inside us. That power of God, through the Holy Spirit, is stronger than anything we can face. There is literally nothing in this world that has more power than God. Not finances, relationship issues, medical problems, nothing! If we live by faith in Him instead of relying on our own strength, we can be confident that we will overcome whatever challenges we face. \r\n\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nThe world is constantly bombarding us with problems and challenges. It\'s easy to look at our circumstances and get discouraged. This verse reminds me that no matter what comes up, God has already won the battle. I need to remember that my God is bigger than anything I can ever face, and trust in His power to overcome. Even when I feel small, insignificant, and unable to fight, God is always there, fighting for me. \r\n\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, thank you for choosing me as your child and always fighting for me. Thank you for this reminder that your power in me is stronger than I can understand. Please help me to see the truth in my circumstances: that You are bigger! Teach me to rely on your strength and not my own. In Jesus\' name, amen. ', 'Promise #26 - Spiritual Warfare', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-26-spiritual-warfare', '', '', '2017-03-28 09:56:10', '2017-03-28 14:56:10', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1101', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1104, 4, '2017-03-28 09:55:35', '2017-03-28 14:55:35', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúHumble yourselves before the Lord and he will lift you up.‚Äù James 4:10\r\n\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nThis verse really ties back to verse 6, which quotes Proverbs 3:34, and says, ‚ÄúGod opposes the proud but shows favor to the humble.‚Äù Verses 6 and 10 are like the bread of a ‚Äúhumility‚Äù sandwich, with verses 7-9 showing us the meat of humility. Humility consists of submission to God (vs. 7), resisting the devil (vs 7), drawing near to God (vs. 8), washing our hands of sin (vs. 8), and grieving (presumably over sin in vs. 9). It ends with the command and promise. The humble will be lifted up.\r\n\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nI tend to think of humility as my relationship to others. For example, don‚Äôt think of myself more highly than I should, or treat others better than myself, serve others, etc. However, this passage refocuses humility on my relationship with God. Am I staying humble before the Lord? My pride wants to say yes, but I can never grow out of submission to Him (vs. 7), resisting the devil (vs. 7) drawing near to God (vs. 8) washing of sin (vs. 8), or grieving sin (vs. 9). While these things might not be ‚Äúfun‚Äù, they‚Äôre worth it because of God‚Äôs promise to lift me up!\r\n\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, I submit to you. I surrender to you. I humble myself before you. I want what you want more than what I want. Thank you for your promises to stand on. Give me the strength to humble myself each day, even when pride gets in the way. In Jesus‚Äô name, Amen.', 'Promise #27 - Humility', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-27-humility', '', '', '2017-03-28 09:55:35', '2017-03-28 14:55:35', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1104', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1106, 4, '2017-03-29 05:00:07', '2017-03-29 10:00:07', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúThe point is this: whoever sows sparingly will also reap sparingly, and whoever sows bountifully will also reap bountifully. Each one must give as he has decided in his heart, not reluctantly or under compulsion, for God loves a cheerful giver.‚Äù - 2 Corinthians 9:6-7\r\n\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nIn Paul\'s letter to the Corinthian church, He echoes the author of Proverbs 3:4 where it states that what one plants, they will harvest that investment. A farmer sows seeds in the field and after the rain nourishes and the sun prepares it, it will bring forth a harvest. And just like the farmer, everyone who gives of their time, talents, and treasures, must decide in their heart to what extent they will give out of a willing  heart rather than under duty or deed.  \r\n\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nMatthew Henry puts it this way, \r\n\r\n\"Money bestowed in charity, may to the carnal mind, seem thrown away, but when given from proper principles, it is seed sown, from which a valuable increase may be expected. It should be given carefully. Giving, like other good works, should be done with thought and design. Due thought, as to our circumstances, and those we are about to relieve, will direct our gifts. It should be given freely, not grudgingly, but cheerfully.‚Äù\r\n\r\nThis passage challenges us to investigate our heart and observe if we are a people of compulsion and duty or of cheerful and freely giving of the resources and gifts God has given to us.  \r\n\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather of heaven and earth, you are the one who gives the seeds and the rains they need and the sunlight to spring forth. You are the one who can look into the depths of my heart and see if I am one who gives liberally of my time, talents and treasures you have entrusted to me. I pray that you will be pleased with my responses to invest cheerfully into the people and things that you have established. If you are not pleased with me, Please forgive me and renew a right spirit of cheerfulness within me. Thank you for showing me the example of Jesus who gave liberally and extensively.  I love you Lord, Amen ', 'Promise #28 - Generosity', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-28-generosity', '', '', '2017-03-28 09:58:29', '2017-03-28 14:58:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1106', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1108, 4, '2017-03-30 05:07:48', '2017-03-30 10:07:48', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúBut he who looks into the perfect law of liberty and continues in it, and is not a forgetful hearer but a doer of the work, this one will be blessed in what he does.\" - James 1:25\r\n\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nObedience is honored.  There are several criteria for the blessing here though. 1. You look into the law of liberty as revealed in the Scriptures. 2. You continue studying, and believing, the scriptures. And 3. You do what it says, not just listen and move on. Then you will be blessed in what you do. This whole chapter in James emphasizes the importance of doing what has been taught, not simply gathering lots and lots of knowledge.  \r\n\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nMy obedience will be honored, but how can I obey if I don\'t know? This shows me the importance of a personal quiet time with the Lord studying scripture. I am a fool if I call myself a Christian,\" little christ,\" and never crack my Bible to learn what Christ taught or did. I am a bigger fool if I do study scripture, and then put it back on the shelf and disobey what it said. Even simply failing to do what is asked of me is disobedience. On the other hand, if I hear and obey, my God will bless what I do. I will have the favor, resources, and ability to magnify the name of my God, and thrive in any situation, just like Joseph in Egypt. And that is worth every ounce of effort I put in. \r\n\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nJesus, thank you for making your life available for us to follow. Thank you that more than 2000 years later I can still imitate you to glorify your name. Guide my study, and show me my gaps. Help me obey the things you teach me, whatever the cost. Help me to believe that you will bless my obedience, and believe that you want me to thrive, not just survive. I love you Jesus. Amen.', 'Promise #29 - Obedience', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-29-obedience', '', '', '2017-03-28 10:08:15', '2017-03-28 15:08:15', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1108', 0, 'post', '', 0),
