(1117, 4, '2017-03-31 10:51:32', '2017-03-31 15:51:32', '<h2>S for Scripture:</h2>\r\n‚ÄúBut I say, walk by the Spirit, and you will not gratify the desires of the flesh.\" - Galatians 5:16\r\n<h2>O for Observation:</h2>\r\nPaul begins this chapter to the Galatians declaring, \"It is for freedom Christ has set us free; stand firm and do not submit again to a yoke of slavery,\" and then describes how the Galatians have fallen back into their old ways before knowing Christ. In verse 16 Paul reveals the secret to living in freedom from our sinful desires: WALKING BY THE SPIRIT! But what does this mean?\r\n\r\nIn <a href=\"https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=John+16%3A7&amp;version=ESV\">John 16:7</a>, Jesus tells his disciples that it is better for them that he go away so that the Holy Spirit would come and later in <a href=\"https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=acts+1%3A4&amp;version=ESV\">Acts 1:4</a>, Jesus tells them to do nothing until they have the gift of the Holy Spirit! So apparently the third person of the Trinity is crucial to our walk with God and living in freedom from sin!\r\n<h2>A for Application:</h2>\r\nI must daily choose to walk in the Spirit submitting to His leading in every step of my day! This means laying aside my plans, desires, and agenda and listening and talking with God in prayer throughout my day. I\'m still learning how to do this, but I\'ve found that when I chat with God throughout my day like I would with my best friend, I am more thankful, joyful, and sensitive to the Holy Spirit\'s leading! The fruit of the Spirit described later in this chapter (<a href=\"https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Galatians+5%3A22-23&amp;version=ESV\">Galatians 5:22-23</a>) are naturally produced and the temptations of the flesh are not even present!\r\n<h2>P for Prayer:</h2>\r\nFather, thank you for the gift of your Holy Spirit and help me to walk daily with Him. I know that your ways and plans are so much better than mine so let me sensitive to your leading every step of my day. Forgive me for the days I try to walk in my own strength with my own agenda and teach me to keep in step with your Holy Spirit! Thank you Lord!', 'Promise #30 - Holy Spirit', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'promise-30-holy-spirit', '', '', '2017-03-31 10:51:32', '2017-03-31 15:51:32', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/?p=1117', 0, 'post', '', 0),
